170static void
171caja_file_init (CajaFile *file)
172{
173 file->details = caja_file_get_instance_private (file);
174
175 caja_file_clear_info (file);
176 caja_file_invalidate_extension_info_internal (file);
177}
178
179static GObject*
180caja_file_constructor (GType type,
181 guint n_construct_properties,
182 GObjectConstructParam *construct_params)
183{
184 GObject *object;
185 CajaFile *file;
186
187 object = (* G_OBJECT_CLASS (caja_file_parent_class)((((GObjectClass*) (void *) ((caja_file_parent_class)))))->constructor) (type,
188 n_construct_properties,
189 construct_params);
190
191 file = CAJA_FILE (object)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((object)))));
192
193 /* Set to default type after full construction */
194 if (CAJA_FILE_GET_CLASS (file)((((CajaFileClass*) (((GTypeInstance*) ((file)))->g_class)
)))->default_file_type != G_FILE_TYPE_UNKNOWN) {
195 file->details->type = CAJA_FILE_GET_CLASS (file)((((CajaFileClass*) (((GTypeInstance*) ((file)))->g_class)
)))->default_file_type;
196 }
197
198 return object;
199}

201gboolean
202caja_file_set_display_name (CajaFile *file,
203 const char *display_name,
204 const char *edit_name,
205 gboolean custom)
206{
207 gboolean changed;
208
209 if (custom && display_name == NULL((void*)0)) {
210 /* We're re-setting a custom display name, invalidate it if
211 we already set it so that the old one is re-read */
212 if (file->details->got_custom_display_name) {
213 file->details->got_custom_display_name = FALSE(0);
214 caja_file_invalidate_attributes (file,
215 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO);
216 }
217 return FALSE(0);
218 }
219
220 if (display_name == NULL((void*)0) || *display_name == 0) {
221 return FALSE(0);
222 }
223
224 if (!custom && file->details->got_custom_display_name) {
225 return FALSE(0);
226 }
227
228 if (edit_name == NULL((void*)0)) {
229 edit_name = display_name;
230 }
231
232 changed = FALSE(0);
233
234 if (eel_strcmp (file->details->display_name, display_name) != 0) {
235 changed = TRUE(!(0));
236
237 g_clear_pointer (&file->details->display_name, g_ref_string_release)do { _Static_assert (sizeof *(&file->details->display_name

275static gboolean
276foreach_metadata_free (gpointer key,
277 gpointer value,
278 gpointer user_data)
279{
280 guint id;
281
282 id = GPOINTER_TO_UINT (key)((guint) (gulong) (key));
283
284 if (id & METADATA_ID_IS_LIST_MASK(1U<<31)) {
285 g_strfreev ((char **)value);
286 } else {
287 g_free ((char *)value);
288 }
289 return TRUE(!(0));
290}
291
292static void
293metadata_hash_free (GHashTable *hash)
294{
295 g_hash_table_foreach_remove (hash,
296 foreach_metadata_free,
297 NULL((void*)0));
298 g_hash_table_destroy (hash);
299}
300
301static gboolean
302metadata_hash_equal (GHashTable *hash1,
303 GHashTable *hash2)
304{
305 GHashTableIter iter;
306 gpointer key1, value1, value2;
307 guint id;
308
309 if (hash1 == NULL((void*)0) && hash2 == NULL((void*)0)) {
310 return TRUE(!(0));
311 }
312
313 if (hash1 == NULL((void*)0) || hash2 == NULL((void*)0)) {
314 return FALSE(0);
315 }
316
317 if (g_hash_table_size (hash1) !=
318 g_hash_table_size (hash2)) {
319 return FALSE(0);
320 }
321
322 g_hash_table_iter_init (&iter, hash1);
323 while (g_hash_table_iter_next (&iter, &key1, &value1)) {
324 value2 = g_hash_table_lookup (hash2, key1);
325 if (value2 == NULL((void*)0)) {
326 return FALSE(0);
327 }
328 id = GPOINTER_TO_UINT (key1)((guint) (gulong) (key1));
329 if (id & METADATA_ID_IS_LIST_MASK(1U<<31)) {
330 if (!eel_g_strv_equal ((char **)value1, (char **)value2)) {
331 return FALSE(0);
332 }
333 } else {
334 if (strcmp ((char *)value1, (char *)value2) != 0) {
335 return FALSE(0);
336 }
337 }
338 }
339
340 return TRUE(!(0));
341}
342
343static void
344clear_metadata (CajaFile *file)
345{
346 if (file->details->metadata) {
347 metadata_hash_free (file->details->metadata);
348 file->details->metadata = NULL((void*)0);
349 }
350}
351
352static GHashTable *
353get_metadata_from_info (GFileInfo *info)
354{
355 GHashTable *metadata;
356 char **attrs;
357 guint id;
358 int i;
359 GFileAttributeType type;
360 gpointer value;
361
362 attrs = g_file_info_list_attributes (info, "metadata");
363
364 metadata = g_hash_table_new (NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
365
366 for (i = 0; attrs[i] != NULL((void*)0); i++) {
367 id = caja_metadata_get_id (attrs[i] + strlen ("metadata::"));
368 if (id == 0) {
369 continue;
370 }
371
372 if (!g_file_info_get_attribute_data (info, attrs[i],
373 &type, &value, NULL((void*)0))) {
374 continue;
375 }
376
377 if (type == G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_TYPE_STRING) {
378 g_hash_table_insert (metadata, GUINT_TO_POINTER (id)((gpointer) (gulong) (id)),
379 g_strdup ((char *)value)g_strdup_inline ((char *)value));
380 } else if (type == G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_TYPE_STRINGV) {
381 id |= METADATA_ID_IS_LIST_MASK(1U<<31);
382 g_hash_table_insert (metadata, GUINT_TO_POINTER (id)((gpointer) (gulong) (id)),
383 g_strdupv ((char **)value));
384 }
385 }
386
387 g_strfreev (attrs);
388
389 return metadata;
390}
391
392gboolean
393caja_file_update_metadata_from_info (CajaFile *file,
394 GFileInfo *info)
395{
396 gboolean changed = FALSE(0);
397
398 if (g_file_info_has_namespace (info, "metadata")) {
399 GHashTable *metadata;
400
401 metadata = get_metadata_from_info (info);
402 if (!metadata_hash_equal (metadata,
403 file->details->metadata)) {
404 changed = TRUE(!(0));
405 clear_metadata (file);
406 file->details->metadata = metadata;
407 } else {
408 metadata_hash_free (metadata);
409 }
410 } else if (file->details->metadata) {
411 changed = TRUE(!(0));
412 clear_metadata (file);
413 }
414 return changed;
415}

547static void
548modify_link_hash_table (CajaFile *file,
549 ModifyListFunction modify_function)
550{
551 char *target_uri;
552 gboolean found;
553 gpointer original_key;
554 GList **list_ptr;
555
556 /* Check if there is a symlink name. If none, we are OK. */
557 if (file->details->symlink_name == NULL((void*)0) || !caja_file_is_symbolic_link (file)) {
558 return;
559 }
560
561 /* Create the hash table first time through. */
562 if (symbolic_links == NULL((void*)0)) {
563 symbolic_links = g_hash_table_new (g_str_hash, g_str_equal);
564 }
565
566 target_uri = caja_file_get_symbolic_link_target_uri (file);
567
568 /* Find the old contents of the hash table. */
569 found = g_hash_table_lookup_extended
570 (symbolic_links, target_uri,
571 &original_key, (gpointer *)&list_ptr);
572 if (!found) {
573 list_ptr = g_new0 (GList *, 1)(GList * *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (1); gsize __s
= sizeof (GList *); gpointer __p; if (__s == 1) __p = g_malloc0
(__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (__n) && (__s ==
0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p =
g_malloc0 (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc0_n (__n, __s); __p
; }));
574 original_key = g_strdup (target_uri)g_strdup_inline (target_uri);
575 g_hash_table_insert (symbolic_links, original_key, list_ptr);
576 }
577 (* modify_function) (list_ptr, file);
578 if (*list_ptr == NULL((void*)0)) {
579 g_hash_table_remove (symbolic_links, target_uri);
580 g_free (list_ptr);
581 g_free (original_key);
582 }
583 g_free (target_uri);
584}
585
586static void
587symbolic_link_weak_notify (gpointer data,
588 GObject *where_the_object_was)
589{
590 GList **list = data;
591 /* This really shouldn't happen, but we're seeing some strange things in
592 bug #358172 where the symlink hashtable isn't correctly updated. */
593 *list = g_list_remove (*list, where_the_object_was);
594}
595
596static void
597add_to_link_hash_table_list (GList **list, CajaFile *file)
598{
599 if (g_list_find (*list, file) != NULL((void*)0)) {
600 g_warning ("Adding file to symlink_table multiple times. "
601 "Please add feedback of what you were doing at https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=358172\n");
602 return;
603 }
604 g_object_weak_ref (G_OBJECT (file)((((GObject*) (void *) ((file))))), symbolic_link_weak_notify, list);
605 *list = g_list_prepend (*list, file);
606}
607
608static void
609add_to_link_hash_table (CajaFile *file)
610{
611 modify_link_hash_table (file, add_to_link_hash_table_list);
612}
613
614static void
615remove_from_link_hash_table_list (GList **list, CajaFile *file)
616{
617 if (g_list_find (*list, file) != NULL((void*)0)) {
618 g_object_weak_unref (G_OBJECT (file)((((GObject*) (void *) ((file))))), symbolic_link_weak_notify, list);
619 *list = g_list_remove (*list, file);
620 }
621}
622
623static void
624remove_from_link_hash_table (CajaFile *file)
625{
626 modify_link_hash_table (file, remove_from_link_hash_table_list);
627}

= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_562

659static CajaFile *
660caja_file_get_internal (GFile *location, gboolean create)
661{
662 gboolean self_owned;
663 CajaDirectory *directory;
664 CajaFile *file;
665 GFile *parent;
666 char *basename;
667
668 g_assert (location != NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_564
; if (location != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_564 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_564
= 0; _g_boolean_var_564; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c", 668, ((const char*) (__func__)
), "location != NULL"); } while (0);

670 parent = g_file_get_parent (location);
671
672 self_owned = FALSE(0);
673 if (parent == NULL((void*)0)) {
674 self_owned = TRUE(!(0));
675 parent = g_object_ref (location)((__typeof__ (location)) (g_object_ref) (location));
676 }
677
678 /* Get object that represents the directory. */
679 directory = caja_directory_get_internal (parent, create);
680
681 g_object_unref (parent);
682
683 /* Get the name for the file. */
684 if (self_owned && directory != NULL((void*)0)) {
685 basename = caja_directory_get_name_for_self_as_new_file (directory);
686 } else {
687 basename = g_file_get_basename (location);
688 }
689 /* Check to see if it's a file that's already known. */
690 if (directory == NULL((void*)0)) {
691 file = NULL((void*)0);
692 } else if (self_owned) {
693 file = directory->details->as_file;
694 } else {
695 file = caja_directory_find_file_by_name (directory, basename);
696 }
697
698 /* Ref or create the file. */
699 if (file != NULL((void*)0)) {
700 caja_file_ref (file);
701 } else if (create && directory != NULL((void*)0)) {
702 file = caja_file_new_from_filename (directory, basename, self_owned);
703 if (self_owned) {
704 g_assert (directory->details->as_file == NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_565
; if (directory->details->as_file == ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_565
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_565 = 0; _g_boolean_var_565; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 704, ((const char*) (__func__)), "directory->details->as_file == NULL"
); } while (0);
705 directory->details->as_file = file;
706 } else {
707 caja_directory_add_file (directory, file);
708 }
709 }
710
711 g_free (basename);
712 caja_directory_unref (directory);
713
714 return file;
715}

1340static void
1341file_stop_callback (GObject *source_object,
1342 GAsyncResult *res,
1343 gpointer callback_data)
1344{
1345 CajaFileOperation *op;
1346 gboolean stopped;
1347 GError *error;
1348
1349 op = callback_data;
1350
1351 error = NULL((void*)0);
1352 stopped = g_drive_stop_finish (G_DRIVE (source_object)((((GDrive*) (void *) ((source_object))))),
1353 res, &error);
1354
1355 if (!stopped &&
1356 error->domain == G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark() &&
1357 (error->code == G_IO_ERROR_FAILED_HANDLED ||
1358 error->code == G_IO_ERROR_CANCELLED)) {
1359 g_error_free (error);
1360 error = NULL((void*)0);
1361 }
1362
1363 caja_file_operation_complete (op, NULL((void*)0), error);
1364 if (error) {
1365 g_error_free (error);
1366 }
1367}

1369void
1370caja_file_stop (CajaFile *file,
1371 GMountOperation *mount_op,
1372 GCancellable *cancellable,
1373 CajaFileOperationCallback callback,
1374 gpointer callback_data)
1375{
1376 GError *error;
1377
1378 if (CAJA_FILE_GET_CLASS (file)((((CajaFileClass*) (((GTypeInstance*) ((file)))->g_class)
)))->stop != NULL((void*)0)) {
1379 if (file->details->can_stop) {
1380 CAJA_FILE_GET_CLASS (file)((((CajaFileClass*) (((GTypeInstance*) ((file)))->g_class)
)))->stop (file, mount_op, cancellable, callback, callback_data);
1381 } else {
1382 if (callback) {
1383 error = NULL((void*)0);
1384 g_set_error_literal (&error, G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED,
1385 _("This file cannot be stopped")dcgettext (((void*)0), "This file cannot be stopped", 5));
1386 callback (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1387 g_error_free (error);
1388 }
1389 }
1390 } else {
1391 GDrive *drive;
1392
1393 drive = NULL((void*)0);
1394 if (file->details->mount != NULL((void*)0))
1395 drive = g_mount_get_drive (file->details->mount);
1396
1397 if (drive != NULL((void*)0) && g_drive_can_stop (drive)) {
1398 CajaFileOperation *op;
1399
1400 op = caja_file_operation_new (file, callback, callback_data);
1401 if (cancellable) {
1402 g_object_unref (op->cancellable);
1403 op->cancellable = g_object_ref (cancellable)((__typeof__ (cancellable)) (g_object_ref) (cancellable));
1404 }
1405
1406 g_drive_stop (drive,
1407 G_MOUNT_UNMOUNT_NONE,
1408 mount_op,
1409 op->cancellable,
1410 file_stop_callback,
1411 op);
1412 } else {
1413 if (callback) {
1414 error = NULL((void*)0);
1415 g_set_error_literal (&error, G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED,
1416 _("This file cannot be stopped")dcgettext (((void*)0), "This file cannot be stopped", 5));
1417 callback (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1418 g_error_free (error);
1419 }
1420 }
1421
1422 if (drive != NULL((void*)0)) {
1423 g_object_unref (drive);
1424 }
1425 }
1426}

1488
1489/**
1490 * caja_file_can_rename:
1491 *
1492 * Check whether the user is allowed to change the name of the file.
1493 *
1494 * @file: The file to check.
1495 *
1496 * Return value: FALSE if the user is definitely not allowed to change
1497 * the name of the file. If the user is allowed to change the name, or
1498 * the code can't tell whether the user is allowed to change the name,
1499 * returns TRUE (so rename failures must always be handled).
1500 */
1501gboolean
1502caja_file_can_rename (CajaFile *file)
1503{
1504 gboolean can_rename;
1505
1506 g_return_val_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file), FALSE)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_585
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_585
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_585 = 0; _g_boolean_var_585; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); return ((0)); } }
while (0);
1507
1508 /* Nonexistent files can't be renamed. */
1509 if (caja_file_is_gone (file)) {
1510 return FALSE(0);
1511 }
1512
1513 /* Self-owned files can't be renamed */
1514 if (caja_file_is_self_owned (file)) {
1515 return FALSE(0);
1516 }
1517
1518 if ((is_desktop_file (file) && !can_rename_desktop_file (file)) ||
1519 caja_file_is_home (file)) {
1520 return FALSE(0);
1521 }
1522
1523 can_rename = TRUE(!(0));
1524
1525 /* Certain types of links can't be renamed */
1526 if (CAJA_IS_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file)); GType __t = (caja_desktop_icon_file_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
1527 CajaDesktopLink *link;
1528
1529 link = caja_desktop_icon_file_get_link (CAJA_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)((((CajaDesktopIconFile*) (void *) ((file))))));
1530
1531 if (link != NULL((void*)0)) {
1532 can_rename = caja_desktop_link_can_rename (link);
1533 g_object_unref (link);
1534 }
1535 }
1536
1537 if (!can_rename) {
1538 return FALSE(0);

1658void
1659caja_file_operation_free (CajaFileOperation *op)
1660{
1661 caja_file_operation_remove (op);
1662 caja_file_unref (op->file);
1663 g_object_unref (op->cancellable);
1664 if (op->free_data) {
1665 op->free_data (op->data);
1666 }
1667 // Start UNDO-REDO
1668 caja_undostack_manager_add_action (caja_undostack_manager_instance(),
1669 op->undo_redo_data);
1670 // End UNDO-REDO
1671 g_free (op);
1672}
1673
1674void
1675caja_file_operation_complete (CajaFileOperation *op, GFile *result_file, GError *error)
1676{
1677 /* Claim that something changed even if the operation failed.
1678 * This makes it easier for some clients who see the "reverting"
1679 * as "changing back".
1680 */
1681 caja_file_operation_remove (op);
1682 caja_file_changed (op->file);
1683 if (op->callback) {
1684 (* op->callback) (op->file, result_file, error, op->callback_data);
1685 }
1686 caja_file_operation_free (op);
1687}
1688
1689void
1690caja_file_operation_cancel (CajaFileOperation *op)
1691{
1692 /* Cancel the operation if it's still in progress. */
1693 g_cancellable_cancel (op->cancellable);
1694}
1695
1696static void
1697rename_get_info_callback (GObject *source_object,
1698 GAsyncResult *res,
1699 gpointer callback_data)
1700{
1701 CajaFileOperation *op;
1702 GFileInfo *new_info;
1703 GError *error;
1704
1705 op = callback_data;
1706
1707 error = NULL((void*)0);
1708 new_info = g_file_query_info_finish (G_FILE (source_object)((((GFile*) (void *) ((source_object))))), res, &error);
1709 if (new_info != NULL((void*)0)) {
1710 CajaDirectory *directory;
1711 CajaFile *existing_file;
1712 char *old_name;
1713 char *old_uri;
1714 char *new_uri;
1715 const char *new_name;
1716
1717 directory = op->file->details->directory;
1718
1719 new_name = g_file_info_get_name (new_info);
1720
1721 /* If there was another file by the same name in this
1722 * directory, mark it gone.
1723 */
1724 existing_file = caja_directory_find_file_by_name (directory, new_name);
1725 if (existing_file != NULL((void*)0)) {
1726 caja_file_mark_gone (existing_file);
1727 caja_file_changed (existing_file);
1728 }
1729
1730 old_uri = caja_file_get_uri (op->file);
1731 old_name = g_strdup (op->file->details->name)g_strdup_inline (op->file->details->name);
1732
1733 update_info_and_name (op->file, new_info);
1734
1735 g_free (old_name);
1736
1737 new_uri = caja_file_get_uri (op->file);
1738 caja_directory_moved (old_uri, new_uri);
1739 g_free (new_uri);
1740 g_free (old_uri);
1741
1742 /* the rename could have affected the display name if e.g.
1743 * we're in a vfolder where the name comes from a desktop file
1744 * and a rename affects the contents of the desktop file.
1745 */
1746 if (op->file->details->got_custom_display_name) {
1747 caja_file_invalidate_attributes (op->file,
1748 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO |
1749 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LINK_INFO);
1750 }
1751
1752 g_object_unref (new_info);
1753 }
1754 caja_file_operation_complete (op, NULL((void*)0), error);
1755 if (error) {
1756 g_error_free (error);
1757 }
1758}
1759
1760static void
1761rename_callback (GObject *source_object,
1762 GAsyncResult *res,
1763 gpointer callback_data)
1764{
1765 CajaFileOperation *op;
1766 GFile *new_file;
1767 GError *error;
1768
1769 op = callback_data;
1770
1771 error = NULL((void*)0);
1772 new_file = g_file_set_display_name_finish (G_FILE (source_object)((((GFile*) (void *) ((source_object))))),
1773 res, &error);
1774
1775 if (new_file != NULL((void*)0)) {
1776 // Start UNDO-REDO
1777 caja_undostack_manager_data_set_rename_information(op->undo_redo_data, G_FILE (source_object)((((GFile*) (void *) ((source_object))))), new_file);
1778 // End UNDO-REDO
1779 g_file_query_info_async (new_file,
1780 CAJA_FILE_DEFAULT_ATTRIBUTES"standard::*,access::*,mountable::*,time::*,unix::*,owner::*,selinux::*,thumbnail::*,id::filesystem,trash::orig-path,trash::deletion-date,metadata::*",
1781 0,
1782 G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT0,
1783 op->cancellable,
1784 rename_get_info_callback, op);
1785 } else {
1786 caja_file_operation_complete (op, NULL((void*)0), error);
1787 g_error_free (error);
1788 }
1789}

1791static gboolean
1792name_is (CajaFile *file, const char *new_name)
1793{
1794 const char *old_name;
1795 old_name = file->details->name;
1796 return strcmp (new_name, old_name) == 0;
1797}
1798
1799void
1800caja_file_rename (CajaFile *file,
1801 const char *new_name,
1802 CajaFileOperationCallback callback,
1803 gpointer callback_data)
1804{
1805 CajaFileOperation *op;
1806 char *old_name;
1807 char *new_file_name;
1808 gboolean success, name_changed;
1809 gboolean is_renameable_desktop_file;
1810 GFile *location;
1811 GError *error;
1812
1813 g_return_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_591
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_591
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_591 = 0; _g_boolean_var_591; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); return; } } while
(0);
1814 g_return_if_fail (new_name != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_592
; if (new_name != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_592 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_592
= 0; _g_boolean_var_592; }), 1))) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning
(((gchar*) 0), ((const char*) (__func__)), "new_name != NULL"
); return; } } while (0);
1815 g_return_if_fail (callback != NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_593
; if (callback != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_593 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_593
= 0; _g_boolean_var_593; }), 1))) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning
(((gchar*) 0), ((const char*) (__func__)), "callback != NULL"
); return; } } while (0);
1816
1817 is_renameable_desktop_file =
1818 is_desktop_file (file) && can_rename_desktop_file (file);
1819
1820 /* Return an error for incoming names containing path separators.
1821 * But not for .desktop files as '/' are allowed for them */
1822 if (strstr (new_name, "/") != NULL((void*)0) && !is_renameable_desktop_file) {
1823 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT,
1824 _("Slashes are not allowed in filenames")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Slashes are not allowed in filenames"
, 5));
1825 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1826 g_error_free (error);
1827 return;
1828 }
1829
1830 /* Can't rename a file that's already gone.
1831 * We need to check this here because there may be a new
1832 * file with the same name.
1833 */
1834 if (caja_file_is_gone (file)) {
1835 /* Claim that something changed even if the rename
1836 * failed. This makes it easier for some clients who
1837 * see the "reverting" to the old name as "changing
1838 * back".
1839 */
1840 caja_file_changed (file);
1841 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_NOT_FOUND,
1842 _("File not found")dcgettext (((void*)0), "File not found", 5));
1843 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1844 g_error_free (error);
1845 return;
1846 }
1847
1848 /* Test the name-hasn't-changed case explicitly, for two reasons.
1849 * (1) rename returns an error if new & old are same.
1850 * (2) We don't want to send file-changed signal if nothing changed.
1851 */
1852 if (!CAJA_IS_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file)); GType __t = (caja_desktop_icon_file_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; })))) &&
1853 !is_renameable_desktop_file &&
1854 name_is (file, new_name)) {
1855 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), callback_data);
1856 return;
1857 }
1858
1859 /* Self-owned files can't be renamed. Test the name-not-actually-changing
1860 * case before this case.
1861 */
1862 if (caja_file_is_self_owned (file)) {
1863 /* Claim that something changed even if the rename
1864 * failed. This makes it easier for some clients who
1865 * see the "reverting" to the old name as "changing
1866 * back".
1867 */
1868 caja_file_changed (file);
1869 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED,
1870 _("Toplevel files cannot be renamed")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Toplevel files cannot be renamed", 5));
1871
1872 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1873 g_error_free (error);
1874 return;
1875 }
1876
1877 if (CAJA_IS_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file)); GType __t = (caja_desktop_icon_file_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
1878 CajaDesktopLink *link;
1879
1880 link = caja_desktop_icon_file_get_link (CAJA_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)((((CajaDesktopIconFile*) (void *) ((file))))));
1881 old_name = caja_file_get_display_name (file);
1882
1883 if ((old_name != NULL((void*)0) && strcmp (new_name, old_name) == 0)) {
1884 success = TRUE(!(0));
1885 } else {
1886 success = (link != NULL((void*)0) && caja_desktop_link_rename (link, new_name));
1887 }
1888
1889 if (success) {
1890 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), callback_data);
1891 } else {
1892 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_FAILED,
1893 _("Unable to rename desktop icon")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Unable to rename desktop icon", 5));
1894 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1895 g_error_free (error);
1896 }
1897
1898 g_free (old_name);
1899 g_object_unref (link);
1900 return;
1901 }
1902
1903 if (is_renameable_desktop_file) {
1904 char *uri;
1905
1906 /* Don't actually change the name if the new name is the same.
1907 * This helps for the vfolder method where this can happen and
1908 * we want to minimize actual changes
1909 */
1910 uri = caja_file_get_uri (file);
1911 old_name = caja_link_local_get_text (uri);
1912 if (old_name != NULL((void*)0) && strcmp (new_name, old_name) == 0) {
1913 success = TRUE(!(0));
1914 name_changed = FALSE(0);
1915 } else {
1916 success = caja_link_local_set_text (uri, new_name);
1917 name_changed = TRUE(!(0));
1918 }
1919 g_free (old_name);
1920 g_free (uri);
1921
1922 if (!success) {
1923 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_FAILED,
1924 _("Unable to rename desktop file")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Unable to rename desktop file", 5));
1925 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
1926 g_error_free (error);
1927 return;
1928 }
1929 if (!g_str_has_suffix(new_name, ".desktop")(__builtin_constant_p (".desktop")? __extension__ ({ const char
* const __str = (new_name); const char * const __suffix = (".desktop"
); gboolean __result = (0); if (__builtin_expect (__extension__
({ int _g_boolean_var_594; if (__str == ((void*)0) || __suffix
== ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_594 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_594
= 0; _g_boolean_var_594; }), 0)) __result = (g_str_has_suffix
) (__str, __suffix); else { const size_t __str_len = strlen (
((__str) + !(__str))); const size_t __suffix_len = strlen (((
__suffix) + !(__suffix))); if (__str_len >= __suffix_len) __result
= memcmp (__str + __str_len - __suffix_len, ((__suffix) + !(
__suffix)), __suffix_len) == 0; } __result; }) : (g_str_has_suffix
) (new_name, ".desktop") ))
1930 new_file_name = g_strdup_printf ("%s.desktop", new_name);
1931 else
1932 new_file_name = g_strdup_printf("%s", new_name);
1933 new_file_name = g_strdelimit (new_file_name, "/", '-');
1934
1935 if (name_is (file, new_file_name)) {
1936 if (name_changed) {
1937 caja_file_invalidate_attributes (file,
1938 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_INFO |
1939 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LINK_INFO);
1940 }
1941
1942 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), callback_data);
1943 g_free (new_file_name);
1944 return;
1945 }
1946 } else {
1947 new_file_name = g_strdup (new_name)g_strdup_inline (new_name);
1948 }
1949
1950 /* Set up a renaming operation. */
1951 op = caja_file_operation_new (file, callback, callback_data);
1952 op->is_rename = TRUE(!(0));
1953
1954 /* Do the renaming. */
1955
1956 location = caja_file_get_location (file);
1957
1958 // Start UNDO-REDO
1959 if (!caja_undostack_manager_is_undo_redo(caja_undostack_manager_instance())) {
1960 op->undo_redo_data = caja_undostack_manager_data_new (CAJA_UNDOSTACK_RENAME, 1);
1961 }
1962 // End UNDO-REDO
1963
1964 g_file_set_display_name_async (location,
1965 new_file_name,
1966 G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT0,
1967 op->cancellable,
1968 rename_callback,
1969 op);
1970 g_free (new_file_name);
1971 g_object_unref (location);
1972}

1974gboolean
1975caja_file_rename_in_progress (CajaFile *file)
1976{

1978 CajaFileOperation *op = NULL((void*)0);
1979
1980 for (node = file->details->operations_in_progress; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
1981 op = node->data;
1982 if (op->is_rename) {
1983 return TRUE(!(0));
1984 }
1985 }
1986 return FALSE(0);

1989void
1990caja_file_cancel (CajaFile *file,
1991 CajaFileOperationCallback callback,
1992 gpointer callback_data)
1993{
1994 GList *node, *next;
1995 CajaFileOperation *op = NULL((void*)0);
1996
1997 for (node = file->details->operations_in_progress; node != NULL((void*)0); node = next) {
1998 next = node->next;
1999 op = node->data;
2000
2001 g_assert (op->file == file)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_595
; if (op->file == file) _g_boolean_var_595 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_595
= 0; _g_boolean_var_595; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c", 2001, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "op->file == file"); } while (0);
2002 if (op->callback == callback && op->callback_data == callback_data) {
2003 caja_file_operation_cancel (op);
2004 }
2005 }

2063static GList *
2064get_link_files (CajaFile *target_file)
2065{
2066 GList **link_files;
2067
2068 if (symbolic_links == NULL((void*)0)) {
2069 link_files = NULL((void*)0);
2070 } else {
2071 char *uri;
2072
2073 uri = caja_file_get_uri (target_file);
2074 link_files = g_hash_table_lookup (symbolic_links, uri);
2075 g_free (uri);
2076 }
2077 if (link_files) {
2078 return caja_file_list_copy (*link_files);
2079 }
2080 return NULL((void*)0);
2081}
2082
2083static void
2084update_links_if_target (CajaFile *target_file)
2085{
2086 GList *link_files, *p;
2087
2088 link_files = get_link_files (target_file);
2089 for (p = link_files; p != NULL((void*)0); p = p->next) {
2090 update_link (CAJA_FILE (p->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((p->data))))), target_file);
2091 }
2092 caja_file_list_free (link_files);
2093}

2710
2711static Knowledge
2712get_item_count (CajaFile *file,
2713 guint *count)
2714{
2715 gboolean known, unreadable;
2716
2717 known = caja_file_get_directory_item_count
2718 (file, count, &unreadable);
2719 if (!known) {
2720 return UNKNOWN;
2721 }
2722 if (unreadable) {
2723 return UNKNOWABLE;
2724 }
2725 return KNOWN;
2726}
2727
2728static Knowledge
2729get_size (CajaFile *file,
2730 goffset *size,
2731 gboolean size_on_disk)
2732{
2733 /* If we tried and failed, then treat it like there is no size
2734 * to know.
2735 */
2736 if (file->details->get_info_failed) {
2737 return UNKNOWABLE;
2738 }
2739
2740 /* If the info is NULL that means we haven't even tried yet,
2741 * so it's just unknown, not unknowable.
2742 */
2743 if (!file->details->got_file_info) {
2744 return UNKNOWN;
2745 }
2746
2747 /* If we got info with no size in it, it means there is no
2748 * such thing as a size as far as mate-vfs is concerned,
2749 * so "unknowable".
2750 */
2751 if (size_on_disk && file->details->size_on_disk == -1) {
2752 return UNKNOWABLE;
2753 }
2754
2755 if (!size_on_disk && file->details->size == -1) {
2756 return UNKNOWABLE;
2757 }
2758
2759 /* We have a size! */
2760 if (size_on_disk) {
2761 *size = file->details->size_on_disk;
2762 } else {
2763 *size = file->details->size;
2764 }
2765
2766 return KNOWN;
2767}
2768
2769static Knowledge
2770get_time (CajaFile *file,
2771 time_t *time_out,
2772 CajaDateType type)
2773{
2774 time_t time;
2775
2776 /* If we tried and failed, then treat it like there is no size
2777 * to know.
2778 */
2779 if (file->details->get_info_failed) {
2780 return UNKNOWABLE;
2781 }
2782
2783 /* If the info is NULL that means we haven't even tried yet,
2784 * so it's just unknown, not unknowable.
2785 */
2786 if (!file->details->got_file_info) {
2787 return UNKNOWN;
2788 }
2789
2790 time = 0;
2791 switch (type) {
2792 case CAJA_DATE_TYPE_MODIFIED:
2793 time = file->details->mtime;
2794 break;
2795 case CAJA_DATE_TYPE_ACCESSED:
2796 time = file->details->atime;
2797 break;
2798 case CAJA_DATE_TYPE_CREATED:
2799 time = file->details->btime;
2800 break;
2801 case CAJA_DATE_TYPE_TRASHED:
2802 time = file->details->trash_time;
2803 break;
2804 default:
2805 g_assert_not_reached ()do { g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c", 2805
, ((const char*) (__func__)), ((void*)0)); } while (0);
2806 break;
2807 }
2808
2809 *time_out = time;
2810
2811 /* If we got info with no modification time in it, it means
2812 * there is no such thing as a modification time as far as
2813 * mate-vfs is concerned, so "unknowable".
2814 */
2815 if (time == 0) {
2816 return UNKNOWABLE;
2817 }
2818 return KNOWN;
2819}
2820
2821static int
2822compare_directories_by_count (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2)
2823{
2824 /* Sort order:
2825 * Directories with unknown # of items
2826 * Directories with "unknowable" # of items
2827 * Directories with 0 items
2828 * Directories with n items
2829 */
2830
2831 Knowledge count_known_1, count_known_2;
2832 guint count_1, count_2;
2833
2834 count_known_1 = get_item_count (file_1, &count_1);
2835 count_known_2 = get_item_count (file_2, &count_2);
2836
2837 if (count_known_1 > count_known_2) {
2838 return -1;
2839 }
2840 if (count_known_1 < count_known_2) {
2841 return +1;
2842 }
2843
2844 /* count_known_1 and count_known_2 are equal now. Check if count
2845 * details are UNKNOWABLE or UNKNOWN.
2846 */
2847 if (count_known_1 == UNKNOWABLE || count_known_1 == UNKNOWN) {
2848 return 0;
2849 }
2850
2851 if (count_1 < count_2) {
2852 return -1;
2853 }
2854 if (count_1 > count_2) {
2855 return +1;
2856 }
2857
2858 return 0;
2859}
2860
2861static int
2862compare_files_by_size (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2, gboolean size_on_disk)
2863{
2864 /* Sort order:
2865 * Files with unknown size.
2866 * Files with "unknowable" size.
2867 * Files with smaller sizes.
2868 * Files with large sizes.
2869 */
2870
2871 Knowledge size_known_1, size_known_2;
2872 goffset size_1 = 0, size_2 = 0;
2873
2874 size_known_1 = get_size (file_1, &size_1, size_on_disk);
2875 size_known_2 = get_size (file_2, &size_2, size_on_disk);
2876
2877 if (size_known_1 > size_known_2) {
2878 return -1;
2879 }
2880 if (size_known_1 < size_known_2) {
2881 return +1;
2882 }
2883
2884 /* size_known_1 and size_known_2 are equal now. Check if size
2885 * details are UNKNOWABLE or UNKNOWN
2886 */
2887 if (size_known_1 == UNKNOWABLE || size_known_1 == UNKNOWN) {
2888 return 0;
2889 }
2890
2891 if (size_1 < size_2) {
2892 return -1;
2893 }
2894 if (size_1 > size_2) {
2895 return +1;
2896 }
2897
2898 return 0;
2899}
2900
2901static int
2902compare_by_size (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2, gboolean size_on_disk)
2903{
2904 /* Sort order:
2905 * Directories with n items
2906 * Directories with 0 items
2907 * Directories with "unknowable" # of items
2908 * Directories with unknown # of items
2909 * Files with large sizes.
2910 * Files with smaller sizes.
2911 * Files with "unknowable" size.
2912 * Files with unknown size.
2913 */
2914
2915 gboolean is_directory_1, is_directory_2;
2916
2917 is_directory_1 = caja_file_is_directory (file_1);
2918 is_directory_2 = caja_file_is_directory (file_2);
2919
2920 if (is_directory_1 && !is_directory_2) {
2921 return -1;
2922 }
2923 if (is_directory_2 && !is_directory_1) {
2924 return +1;
2925 }
2926
2927 if (is_directory_1) {
2928 return compare_directories_by_count (file_1, file_2);
2929 } else {
2930 return compare_files_by_size (file_1, file_2, size_on_disk);
2931 }
2932}
2933
2934static int
2935compare_by_display_name (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2)
2936{
2937 const char *name_1, *name_2;
2938 const char *key_1, *key_2;
2939 gboolean sort_last_1, sort_last_2;
2940 int compare;
2941
2942 name_1 = caja_file_peek_display_name (file_1);
2943 name_2 = caja_file_peek_display_name (file_2);
2944
2945 sort_last_1 = name_1[0] == SORT_LAST_CHAR1'.' || name_1[0] == SORT_LAST_CHAR2'#';
2946 sort_last_2 = name_2[0] == SORT_LAST_CHAR1'.' || name_2[0] == SORT_LAST_CHAR2'#';
2947
2948 if (sort_last_1 && !sort_last_2) {
2949 compare = +1;
2950 } else if (!sort_last_1 && sort_last_2) {
2951 compare = -1;
2952 } else {
2953 key_1 = caja_file_peek_display_name_collation_key (file_1);
2954 key_2 = caja_file_peek_display_name_collation_key (file_2);
2955 compare = strcmp (key_1, key_2);
2956 }
2957
2958 return compare;
2959}
2960
2961static int
2962compare_by_directory_name (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2)
2963{
2964 char *directory_1, *directory_2;
2965 int compare;
2966
2967 if (file_1->details->directory == file_2->details->directory) {
2968 return 0;
2969 }
2970
2971 directory_1 = caja_file_get_parent_uri_for_display (file_1);

2995static GList *
2996prepend_automatic_keywords (CajaFile *file,
2997 GList *names)
2998{
2999 /* Prepend in reverse order. */
3000 CajaFile *parent;
3001
3002 parent = caja_file_get_parent (file);
3003
3004#ifdef TRASH_IS_FAST_ENOUGH
3005 if (caja_file_is_in_trash (file)) {
3006 names = g_list_prepend
3007 (names, g_strdup (CAJA_FILE_EMBLEM_NAME_TRASH)g_strdup_inline ("trash"));
3008 }
3009#endif
3010 if (file_has_note (file)) {
3011 names = g_list_prepend
3012 (names, g_strdup (CAJA_FILE_EMBLEM_NAME_NOTE)g_strdup_inline ("note"));
3013 }
3014
3015 /* Trash files are assumed to be read-only,
3016 * so we want to ignore them here. */
3017 if (!caja_file_can_write (file) &&
3018 !caja_file_is_in_trash (file) &&
3019 (parent == NULL((void*)0) || caja_file_can_write (parent))) {
3020 names = g_list_prepend
3021 (names, g_strdup (CAJA_FILE_EMBLEM_NAME_CANT_WRITE)g_strdup_inline ("nowrite"));
3022 }
3023 if (!caja_file_can_read (file)) {
3024 names = g_list_prepend
3025 (names, g_strdup (CAJA_FILE_EMBLEM_NAME_CANT_READ)g_strdup_inline ("noread"));
3026 }
3027 if (caja_file_is_symbolic_link (file)) {
3028 names = g_list_prepend
3029 (names, g_strdup (CAJA_FILE_EMBLEM_NAME_SYMBOLIC_LINK)g_strdup_inline ("symbolic-link"));
3030 }
3031
3032 if (parent) {
3033 caja_file_unref (parent);
3034 }
3035

3039static void
3040fill_emblem_cache_if_needed (CajaFile *file)
3041{
3042 GList *node, *keywords;
3043 char *scanner;
3044 size_t length;
3045
3046 if (file->details->compare_by_emblem_cache != NULL((void*)0)) {
3047 /* Got a cache already. */
3048 return;
3049 }
3050
3051 keywords = caja_file_get_keywords (file);
3052
3053 /* Add up the keyword string lengths */
3054 length = 1;
3055 for (node = keywords; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
3056 length += strlen ((const char *) node->data) + 1;
3057 }
3058
3059 /* Now that we know how large the cache struct needs to be, allocate it. */
3060 file->details->compare_by_emblem_cache = g_malloc (sizeof(CajaFileSortByEmblemCache) + length);
3061
3062 /* Copy them into the cache. */
3063 scanner = file->details->compare_by_emblem_cache->emblem_keywords;
3064 for (node = keywords; node != NULL((void*)0); node = node->next) {
3065 length = strlen ((const char *) node->data) + 1;
3066 memcpy (scanner, (const char *) node->data, length);
3067 scanner += length;
3068 }
3069
3070 /* Zero-terminate so we can tell where the list ends. */
3071 *scanner = 0;
3072
3073 g_list_free_full (keywords, g_free);
3074}

3099 keyword_cache_1 += length + 1;
3100 keyword_cache_2 += length + 1;

3103 /* One or both is now NULL. */
3104 if (*keyword_cache_1 != '\0') {
3105 g_assert (*keyword_cache_2 == '\0')do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_607
; if (*keyword_cache_2 == '\0') _g_boolean_var_607 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_607
= 0; _g_boolean_var_607; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c", 3105, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "*keyword_cache_2 == '\\0'"); } while (0);
3106 return -1;
3107 } else if (*keyword_cache_2 != '\0') {
3108 return +1;

3110
3111 return 0;

3114static int
3115compare_by_type (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2)
3116{
3117 gboolean is_directory_1;
3118 gboolean is_directory_2;
3119 char *type_string_1;
3120 char *type_string_2;
3121 int result;
3122
3123 /* Directories go first. Then, if mime types are identical,
3124 * don't bother getting strings (for speed). This assumes
3125 * that the string is dependent entirely on the mime type,
3126 * which is true now but might not be later.
3127 */
3128 is_directory_1 = caja_file_is_directory (file_1);
3129 is_directory_2 = caja_file_is_directory (file_2);
3130
3131 if (is_directory_1 && is_directory_2) {
3132 return 0;
3133 }
3134
3135 if (is_directory_1) {
3136 return -1;
3137 }
3138
3139 if (is_directory_2) {
3140 return +1;
3141 }
3142
3143 if (file_1->details->mime_type != NULL((void*)0) &&
3144 file_2->details->mime_type != NULL((void*)0) &&
3145 strcmp (file_1->details->mime_type,
3146 file_2->details->mime_type) == 0) {
3147 return 0;
3148 }
3149
3150 type_string_1 = caja_file_get_type_as_string (file_1);
3151 type_string_2 = caja_file_get_type_as_string (file_2);
3152
3153 result = g_utf8_collate (type_string_1, type_string_2);
3154
3155 g_free (type_string_1);
3156 g_free (type_string_2);
3157
3158 return result;

3161static int
3162compare_by_time (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2, CajaDateType type)
3163{
3164 /* Sort order:
3165 * Files with unknown times.
3166 * Files with "unknowable" times.
3167 * Files with older times.
3168 * Files with newer times.
3169 */
3170
3171 Knowledge time_known_1, time_known_2;
3172 time_t time_1, time_2;
3173
3174 time_1 = 0;
3175 time_2 = 0;
3176
3177 time_known_1 = get_time (file_1, &time_1, type);
3178 time_known_2 = get_time (file_2, &time_2, type);
3179
3180 if (time_known_1 > time_known_2) {
3181 return -1;
3182 }
3183 if (time_known_1 < time_known_2) {
3184 return +1;
3185 }
3186
3187 /* Now time_known_1 is equal to time_known_2. Check whether
3188 * we failed to get modification times for files
3189 */
3190 if(time_known_1 == UNKNOWABLE || time_known_1 == UNKNOWN) {
3191 return 0;
3192 }
3193
3194 if (time_1 < time_2) {
3195 return -1;
3196 }
3197 if (time_1 > time_2) {
3198 return +1;
3199 }
3200
3201 return 0;
3202}

3206{

3208
3209 compare = compare_by_directory_name (file_1, file_2);
3210 if (compare != 0) {
3211 return compare;
3212 }
3213 return compare_by_display_name (file_1, file_2);

3215
3216/* prev_extension_segment:
3217 * @basename The basename of a file
3218 * @rem_chars A pointer to the amount of remaining characters
3219 *
3220 * Finds the next segment delimiter to the left. A starting character of '.' is
3221 * set to '\0'.
3222 *
3223 * Return value: The start of the previous segment (right of the dot) or
3224 * basename if there are none remaining.
3225 */
3226static char *
3227prev_extension_segment (char *basename, int *rem_chars)
3228{
3229 if (*basename == '.') {
3230 *basename = 0;
3231 basename--;
3232 (*rem_chars)--;
3233 }
3234
3235 while (*rem_chars > 0 && *basename != '.') {
3236 (*rem_chars)--;
3237 basename--;
3238 }
3239
3240 return basename + 1;
3241}
3242
3243/* is_valid_extension_segment:
3244 * @segment Part of a modifiable zero-terminated string
3245 * @segment_index The index of the current segment
3246 *
3247 * Uses a heuristic to identify valid file extensions.
3248 *
3249 * Return value: Whether the segment is part of the file extension.
3250 */
3251static gboolean
3252is_valid_extension_segment (const char *segment, int segment_index)
3253{
3254 gboolean result;
3255 gboolean has_letters;
3256 int char_offset;
3257 switch (segment_index) {
3258 case 0:
3259 /* extremely long segments are probably not part of the extension */
3260 result = strlen (segment) < 20;
3261 break;
3262 default:
3263 has_letters = FALSE(0);
3264 char_offset = 0;
3265 while (TRUE(!(0))) {
3266 char c;
3267
3268 c = *(segment + char_offset);
3269 if (c == '\0') {
3270 result = has_letters;
3271 break;
3272 }
3273 /* allow digits if there are also letters */
3274 else if (isalpha (c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _ISalpha
)) {
3275 has_letters = TRUE(!(0));
3276 }
3277 /* fail if it is neither digit nor letter */
3278 else if (!isdigit (c)((*__ctype_b_loc ())[(int) ((c))] & (unsigned short int) _ISdigit
)) {
3279 result = FALSE(0);
3280 break;
3281 }
3282
3283 if (char_offset >= SORT_BY_EXTENSION_FOLLOWING_MAX_LENGTH3) {
3284 result = FALSE(0);
3285 break;
3286 }
3287 char_offset++;
3288 }
3289 }
3290 return result;
3291}
3292
3293static int
3294compare_by_extension_segments (CajaFile *file_1, CajaFile *file_2)
3295{
3296 char *name_1, *name_2;
3297 char *segment_1, *segment_2;
3298 int compare;
3299 int rem_chars_1, rem_chars_2;
3300 gboolean done_1, done_2;
3301 gboolean is_directory_1, is_directory_2;
3302 int segment_index;
3303
3304 /* Directories do not have an extension */
3305 is_directory_1 = caja_file_is_directory (file_1);
3306 is_directory_2 = caja_file_is_directory (file_2);
3307
3308 if (is_directory_1 && is_directory_2) {
3309 return 0;
3310 } else if (is_directory_1) {
3311 return -1;
3312 } else if (is_directory_2) {
3313 return 1;
3314 }
3315
3316 name_1 = caja_file_get_display_name (file_1);
3317 name_2 = caja_file_get_display_name (file_2);
3318 rem_chars_1 = strlen (name_1);
3319 rem_chars_2 = strlen (name_2);
3320
3321 /* Point to one after the zero character */
3322 segment_1 = name_1 + rem_chars_1 + 1;
3323 segment_2 = name_2 + rem_chars_2 + 1;
3324
3325 segment_index = 0;
3326 do {
3327 segment_1 = prev_extension_segment (segment_1 - 1, &rem_chars_1);
3328 segment_2 = prev_extension_segment (segment_2 - 1, &rem_chars_2);
3329
3330 done_1 = rem_chars_1 <= 0 || !is_valid_extension_segment (segment_1, segment_index);
3331 done_2 = rem_chars_2 <= 0 || !is_valid_extension_segment (segment_2, segment_index);
3332 if (done_1 && !done_2) {
3333 compare = -1;
3334 break;
3335 }
3336 else if (!done_1 && done_2) {
3337 compare = 1;
3338 break;
3339 }
3340 else if (done_1 && done_2) {
3341 compare = 0;
3342 break;
3343 }
3344
3345 segment_index++;
3346 if (segment_index > SORT_BY_EXTENSION_MAX_SEGMENTS3 - 1) {
3347 break;
3348 }
3349 compare = strcmp (segment_1, segment_2);
3350 } while (compare == 0);
3351
3352 g_free (name_1);
3353 g_free (name_2);
3354
3355 return compare;
3356}

3399static int
3400caja_file_compare_for_sort_internal (CajaFile *file_1,
3401 CajaFile *file_2,
3402 gboolean directories_first,
3403 gboolean reversed)
3404{
3405 gboolean is_directory_1, is_directory_2;
3406
3407 if (directories_first) {
3408 is_directory_1 = caja_file_is_directory (file_1);
3409 is_directory_2 = caja_file_is_directory (file_2);
3410
3411 if (is_directory_1 && !is_directory_2) {
3412 return -1;
3413 }
3414
3415 if (is_directory_2 && !is_directory_1) {
3416 return +1;
3417 }
3418 }
3419
3420 if (file_1->details->sort_order < file_2->details->sort_order) {
3421 return reversed ? 1 : -1;
3422 } else if (file_1->details->sort_order > file_2->details->sort_order) {
3423 return reversed ? -1 : 1;
3424 }
3425
3426 return 0;
3427}
3428
3429/**
3430 * caja_file_compare_for_sort:
3431 * @file_1: A file object
3432 * @file_2: Another file object
3433 * @sort_type: Sort criterion
3434 * @directories_first: Put all directories before any non-directories
3435 * @reversed: Reverse the order of the items, except that
3436 * the directories_first flag is still respected.
3437 *
3438 * Return value: int < 0 if @file_1 should come before file_2 in a
3439 * sorted list; int > 0 if @file_2 should come before file_1 in a
3440 * sorted list; 0 if @file_1 and @file_2 are equal for this sort criterion. Note
3441 * that each named sort type may actually break ties several ways, with the name
3442 * of the sort criterion being the primary but not only differentiator.
3443 **/
3444int
3445caja_file_compare_for_sort (CajaFile *file_1,
3446 CajaFile *file_2,
3447 CajaFileSortType sort_type,
3448 gboolean directories_first,
3449 gboolean reversed)
3450{
3451 int result;
3452
3453 if (file_1 == file_2) {
3454 return 0;
3455 }
3456
3457 result = caja_file_compare_for_sort_internal (file_1, file_2, directories_first, reversed);
3458
3459 if (result == 0) {
3460 switch (sort_type) {
3461 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME:
3462 result = compare_by_display_name (file_1, file_2);
3463 if (result == 0) {
3464 result = compare_by_directory_name (file_1, file_2);
3465 }
3466 break;
3467 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DIRECTORY:
3468 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3469 break;
3470 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_SIZE:
3471 /* Compare directory sizes ourselves, then if necessary
3472 * use MateVFS to compare file sizes.
3473 */
3474 result = compare_by_size (file_1, file_2, FALSE(0));
3475 if (result == 0) {
3476 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3477 }
3478 break;
3479 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_SIZE_ON_DISK:
3480 /* Compare directory sizes ourselves, then if necessary
3481 * use MateVFS to compare file sizes.
3482 */
3483 result = compare_by_size (file_1, file_2, TRUE(!(0)));
3484 if (result == 0) {
3485 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3486 }
3487 break;
3488 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_TYPE:
3489 /* MateVFS doesn't know about our special text for certain
3490 * mime types, so we handle the mime-type sorting ourselves.
3491 */
3492 result = compare_by_type (file_1, file_2);
3493 if (result == 0) {
3494 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3495 }
3496 break;
3497 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_MTIME:
3498 result = compare_by_time (file_1, file_2, CAJA_DATE_TYPE_MODIFIED);
3499 if (result == 0) {
3500 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3501 }
3502 break;
3503 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_BTIME:
3504 result = compare_by_time (file_1, file_2, CAJA_DATE_TYPE_CREATED);
3505 if (result == 0) {
3506 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3507 }
3508 break;
3509 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_ATIME:
3510 result = compare_by_time (file_1, file_2, CAJA_DATE_TYPE_ACCESSED);
3511 if (result == 0) {
3512 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3513 }
3514 break;
3515 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_TRASHED_TIME:
3516 result = compare_by_time (file_1, file_2, CAJA_DATE_TYPE_TRASHED);
3517 if (result == 0) {
3518 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3519 }
3520 break;
3521 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_EMBLEMS:
3522 /* MateVFS doesn't know squat about our emblems, so
3523 * we handle comparing them here, before falling back
3524 * to tie-breakers.
3525 */
3526 result = compare_by_emblems (file_1, file_2);
3527 if (result == 0) {
3528 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3529 }
3530 break;
3531 case CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_EXTENSION:
3532 result = compare_by_extension_segments (file_1, file_2);
3533 if (result == 0) {
3534 result = compare_by_full_path (file_1, file_2);
3535 }
3536 break;
3537 default:
3538 g_return_val_if_reached (0)do { g_log (((gchar*) 0), G_LOG_LEVEL_CRITICAL, "file %s: line %d (%s): should not be reached"
, "caja-file.c", 3538, ((const char*) (__func__))); return (0
); } while (0);
3539 }
3540
3541 if (reversed) {
3542 result = -result;
3543 }
3544 }
3545
3546 return result;
3547}
3548
3549int
3550caja_file_compare_for_sort_by_attribute_q (CajaFile *file_1,
3551 CajaFile *file_2,
3552 GQuark attribute,
3553 gboolean directories_first,
3554 gboolean reversed)
3555{
3556 int result;
3557
3558 if (file_1 == file_2) {
3559 return 0;
3560 }
3561
3562 /* Convert certain attributes into CajaFileSortTypes and use
3563 * caja_file_compare_for_sort()
3564 */
3565 if (attribute == 0 || attribute == attribute_name_q) {
3566 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3567 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME,
3568 directories_first,
3569 reversed);
3570 } else if (attribute == attribute_size_q) {
3571 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3572 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_SIZE,
3573 directories_first,
3574 reversed);
3575 } else if (attribute == attribute_size_on_disk_q) {
3576 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3577 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_SIZE_ON_DISK,
3578 directories_first,
3579 reversed);
3580 } else if (attribute == attribute_type_q) {
3581 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3582 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_TYPE,
3583 directories_first,
3584 reversed);
3585 } else if (attribute == attribute_modification_date_q || attribute == attribute_date_modified_q) {
3586 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3587 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_MTIME,
3588 directories_first,
3589 reversed);
3590 } else if (attribute == attribute_creation_date_q || attribute == attribute_date_created_q) {
3591 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3592 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_BTIME,
3593 directories_first,
3594 reversed);
3595 } else if (attribute == attribute_accessed_date_q || attribute == attribute_date_accessed_q) {
3596 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3597 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_ATIME,
3598 directories_first,
3599 reversed);
3600 } else if (attribute == attribute_trashed_on_q) {
3601 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3602 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_TRASHED_TIME,
3603 directories_first,
3604 reversed);
3605 } else if (attribute == attribute_emblems_q) {
3606 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3607 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_EMBLEMS,
3608 directories_first,
3609 reversed);
3610 } else if (attribute == attribute_extension_q) {
3611 return caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2,
3612 CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_EXTENSION,
3613 directories_first,
3614 reversed);
3615 }
3616
3617 /* it is a normal attribute, compare by strings */
3618
3619 result = caja_file_compare_for_sort_internal (file_1, file_2, directories_first, reversed);
3620
3621 if (result == 0) {
3622 char *value_1;
3623 char *value_2;
3624
3625 value_1 = caja_file_get_string_attribute_q (file_1,
3626 attribute);
3627 value_2 = caja_file_get_string_attribute_q (file_2,
3628 attribute);
3629
3630 if (value_1 != NULL((void*)0) && value_2 != NULL((void*)0)) {
3631 result = strcmp (value_1, value_2);
3632 }
3633
3634 g_free (value_1);
3635 g_free (value_2);
3636
3637 if (reversed) {
3638 result = -result;
3639 }
3640 }
3641
3642 return result;
3643}

3648 const char *attribute,
3649 gboolean directories_first,
3650 gboolean reversed)
3651{
3652 return caja_file_compare_for_sort_by_attribute_q (file_1, file_2,
3653 g_quark_from_string (attribute),
3654 directories_first,
3655 reversed);

3692/**
3693 * caja_file_should_show:
3694 * @file: the file to check.
3695 * @show_hidden: whether we want to show hidden files or not.
3696 * @show_backup: whether we want to show backup files or not.
3697 *
3698 * Determines if a #CajaFile should be shown. Note that when browsing
3699 * a trash directory, this function will always return %TRUE.
3700 *
3701 * Returns: %TRUE if the file should be shown, %FALSE if it shouldn't.
3702 */
3703gboolean
3704caja_file_should_show (CajaFile *file,
3705 gboolean show_hidden,
3706 gboolean show_foreign,
3707 gboolean show_backup)
3708{
3709 /* Never hide any files in trash. */
3710 if (caja_file_is_in_trash (file)) {
3711 return TRUE(!(0));
3712 } else {
3713 return (show_hidden || !caja_file_is_hidden_file (file)) &&
3714 (show_backup || !caja_file_is_backup_file (file)) &&
3715 (show_foreign || !(caja_file_is_in_desktop (file) && caja_file_is_foreign_link (file)));
3716 }
3717}

3961static gboolean
3962get_time_from_time_string (const char *time_string,
3963 time_t *time)
3964{
3965 long scanned_time;
3966 char c;
3967
3968 g_assert (time != NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_628
; if (time != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_628 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_628
= 0; _g_boolean_var_628; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c", 3968, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "time != NULL"); } while (0);
3969
3970 /* Only accept string if it has one integer with nothing
3971 * afterwards.
3972 */
3973 if (time_string == NULL((void*)0) ||
3974 sscanf (time_string, "%ld%c", &scanned_time, &c) != 1) {
3975 return FALSE(0);
3976 }
3977 *time = (time_t) scanned_time;

3982caja_file_get_time_metadata (CajaFile *file,
3983 const char *key)
3984{

3990 time = UNDEFINED_TIME((time_t) (-1));

4063
4064static const char *
4065caja_file_peek_display_name (CajaFile *file)
4066{
4067 /*
4068 stefano-k: Imported 15_nautilus_file_peek_crash.patch from debian nautilus
4069 Date: Thu, 27 Jan 2011 10:22:10 +0000
4070 Subject: Prevent a crash in nautilus_file_peek_display_name() on invalid NautilusFile
4071 This is more a workaround only, expect assert failures at other
4072 places when something bad happens. There's a race condition somewhere,
4073 this patch only prevents immediate crash.
4074 Patch by Marcus Husar <marcus.husar@rose.uni-heidelberg.de>
4075 https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=602500
4076 */
4077 if (file == NULL((void*)0) || caja_file_is_gone (file))
4078 return "";
4079
4080 /* Default to display name based on filename if its not set yet */
4081
4082 if (file->details->display_name == NULL((void*)0)) {
4083 const char *name;
4084
4085 name = file->details->name;
4086 if (g_utf8_validate (name, -1, NULL((void*)0))) {
4087 caja_file_set_display_name (file,
4088 name,
4089 NULL((void*)0),
4090 FALSE(0));
4091 } else {
4092 char *escaped_name;
4093
4094 escaped_name = g_uri_escape_string (name, G_URI_RESERVED_CHARS_ALLOWED_IN_PATH"!$&'()*+,;=" ":@" "/", TRUE(!(0)));
4095 caja_file_set_display_name (file,
4096 escaped_name,
4097 NULL((void*)0),
4098 FALSE(0));
4099 g_free (escaped_name);
4100 }
4101 }
4102
4103 return file->details->display_name;
4104}

4278static char *
4279get_custom_icon_metadata_uri (CajaFile *file)
4280{

4285 if (uri != NULL((void*)0) &&

4299
4300static GIcon *
4301get_custom_icon (CajaFile *file)
4302{
4303 char *custom_icon_uri;
4304 GFile *icon_file;
4305 GIcon *icon;
4306
4307 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
4308 return NULL((void*)0);
4309 }
4310
4311 icon = NULL((void*)0);
4312
4313 /* Metadata takes precedence */
4314 custom_icon_uri = get_custom_icon_metadata_uri (file);
4315
4316 if (custom_icon_uri) {
4317 icon_file = g_file_new_for_uri (custom_icon_uri);
4318 icon = g_file_icon_new (icon_file);
4319 g_object_unref (icon_file);
4320 g_free (custom_icon_uri);
4321 }
4322
4323 if (icon == NULL((void*)0) && file->details->got_link_info && file->details->custom_icon != NULL((void*)0)) {
4324 if (g_path_is_absolute (file->details->custom_icon)) {
4325 icon_file = g_file_new_for_path (file->details->custom_icon);
4326 icon = g_file_icon_new (icon_file);
4327 g_object_unref (icon_file);
4328 } else {
4329 icon = g_themed_icon_new (file->details->custom_icon);
4330 }
4331 }
4332
4333 return icon;
4334}

4336static guint64 cached_thumbnail_limit;
4337int cached_thumbnail_size;
4338static int show_image_thumbs;
4339
4340GFilesystemPreviewType
4341caja_file_get_filesystem_use_preview (CajaFile *file)
4342{
4343 GFilesystemPreviewType use_preview;

4345

4347 if (parent != NULL((void*)0)) {

4356
4357gboolean
4358caja_file_should_show_thumbnail (CajaFile *file)
4359{
4360 const char *mime_type;
4361 GFilesystemPreviewType use_preview;
4362
4363 use_preview = caja_file_get_filesystem_use_preview (file);
4364
4365 mime_type = file->details->mime_type;
4366 if (mime_type == NULL((void*)0)) {
4367 mime_type = "application/octet-stream";
4368 }
4369
4370 /* If the thumbnail has already been created, don't care about the size
4371 * of the original file.
4372 */
4373 if (caja_thumbnail_is_mimetype_limited_by_size (mime_type) &&
4374 file->details->thumbnail_path == NULL((void*)0) &&
4375 caja_file_get_size (file) > cached_thumbnail_limit) {
4376 return FALSE(0);
4377 }
4378
4379 if (show_image_thumbs == CAJA_SPEED_TRADEOFF_ALWAYS) {
4380 if (use_preview == G_FILESYSTEM_PREVIEW_TYPE_NEVER) {
4381 return FALSE(0);
4382 } else {
4383 return TRUE(!(0));
4384 }
4385 } else if (show_image_thumbs == CAJA_SPEED_TRADEOFF_NEVER) {
4386 return FALSE(0);
4387 } else {
4388 if (use_preview == G_FILESYSTEM_PREVIEW_TYPE_NEVER) {
4389 /* file system says to never thumbnail anything */
4390 return FALSE(0);
4391 } else if (use_preview == G_FILESYSTEM_PREVIEW_TYPE_IF_LOCAL) {
4392 /* file system says we should treat file as if it's local */
4393 return TRUE(!(0));
4394 } else {
4395 /* only local files */
4396 return caja_file_is_local (file);
4397 }
4398 }
4399
4400 return FALSE(0);
4401}

4404prepend_icon_name (const char *name,

4406{
4407 g_themed_icon_prepend_name(icon, name);
4408}
4409
4410GIcon *
4411caja_file_get_gicon (CajaFile *file,
4412 CajaFileIconFlags flags)
4413{
4414 const char * const * names;
4415 GIcon *icon, *mount_icon = NULL((void*)0), *emblemed_icon;
4416 gboolean is_folder = FALSE(0), is_preview = FALSE(0), is_inode_directory = FALSE(0);
4417
4418 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
4419 return NULL((void*)0);
4420 }
4421
4422 icon = get_custom_icon (file);
4423 if (icon != NULL((void*)0)) {
4424 return icon;
4425 }
4426
4427 if (file->details->icon) {
4428 icon = NULL((void*)0);
4429
4430 /* fetch the mount icon here, we'll use it later */
4431 if (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_MOUNT_ICON ||
4432 flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_MOUNT_ICON_AS_EMBLEM) {
4433 GMount *mount;
4434
4435 mount = caja_file_get_mount (file);
4436
4437 if (mount != NULL((void*)0)) {
4438 mount_icon = g_mount_get_icon (mount);
4439 g_object_unref (mount);
4440 }
4441 }
4442
4443 if (((flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_EMBEDDING_TEXT) ||
4444 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_FOR_DRAG_ACCEPT) ||
4445 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_FOR_OPEN_FOLDER) ||
4446 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_MOUNT_ICON) ||
4447 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_MOUNT_ICON_AS_EMBLEM) ||
4448 ((flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_IGNORE_VISITING) == 0 &&
4449 caja_file_has_open_window (file))) &&
4450 G_IS_THEMED_ICON (file->details->icon)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file->details->icon)); GType __t = ((g_themed_icon_get_type
())); gboolean __r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->
g_class && __inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r =
(!(0)); else __r = g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t);
__r; }))))) {
4451 GPtrArray *prepend_array;
4452 int i;
4453
4454 names = g_themed_icon_get_names (G_THEMED_ICON (file->details->icon)((((GThemedIcon*) (void *) ((file->details->icon))))));
4455 prepend_array = g_ptr_array_new ();
4456
4457 for (i = 0; names[i] != NULL((void*)0); i++) {
4458 const char *name;
4459
4460 name = names[i];
4461
4462 if (strcmp (name, "folder") == 0) {
4463 is_folder = TRUE(!(0));
4464 }
4465 if (strcmp (name, "inode-directory") == 0) {
4466 is_inode_directory = TRUE(!(0));
4467 }
4468 if (strcmp (name, "text-x-generic") == 0 &&
4469 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_EMBEDDING_TEXT)) {
4470 is_preview = TRUE(!(0));
4471 }
4472 }
4473
4474 /* Here, we add icons in reverse order of precedence,
4475 * because they are later prepended */
4476 if (is_preview) {
4477 g_ptr_array_add (prepend_array, "text-x-preview");
4478 }
4479
4480 /* "folder" should override "inode-directory", not the other way around */
4481 if (is_inode_directory) {
4482 g_ptr_array_add (prepend_array, "folder");
4483 }
4484 if (is_folder && (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_FOR_OPEN_FOLDER)) {
4485 g_ptr_array_add (prepend_array, "folder-open");
4486 }
4487 if (is_folder &&
4488 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_IGNORE_VISITING) == 0 &&
4489 caja_file_has_open_window (file)) {
4490 g_ptr_array_add (prepend_array, "folder-visiting");
4491 }
4492 if (is_folder &&
4493 (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_FOR_DRAG_ACCEPT)) {
4494 g_ptr_array_add (prepend_array, "folder-drag-accept");
4495 }
4496
4497 if (prepend_array->len) {
4498 /* When constructing GThemed Icon, pointers from the array
4499 * are reused, but not the array itself, so the cast is safe */
4500 icon = g_themed_icon_new_from_names ((char**) names, -1);
4501 g_ptr_array_foreach (prepend_array, (GFunc) prepend_icon_name, icon);
4502 }
4503
4504 g_ptr_array_free (prepend_array, TRUE(!(0)));
4505 }
4506
4507 if (icon == NULL((void*)0)) {
4508 icon = g_object_ref (file->details->icon)((__typeof__ (file->details->icon)) (g_object_ref) (file
->details->icon));
4509 }
4510
4511 if ((flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_MOUNT_ICON) &&
4512 mount_icon != NULL((void*)0)) {
4513 g_object_unref (icon);
4514 icon = mount_icon;
4515 } else if ((flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_MOUNT_ICON_AS_EMBLEM) &&
4516 mount_icon != NULL((void*)0) && !g_icon_equal (mount_icon, icon)) {
4517 GEmblem *emblem;
4518
4519 emblem = g_emblem_new (mount_icon);
4520 emblemed_icon = g_emblemed_icon_new (icon, emblem);
4521
4522 g_object_unref (emblem);
4523 g_object_unref (icon);
4524 g_object_unref (mount_icon);
4525
4526 icon = emblemed_icon;
4527 } else if (mount_icon != NULL((void*)0)) {
4528 g_object_unref (mount_icon);
4529 }
4530
4531 return icon;
4532 }
4533
4534 return g_themed_icon_new ("text-x-generic");
4535}

4537static GIcon *
4538get_default_file_icon (CajaFileIconFlags flags)
4539{
4540 static GIcon *fallback_icon = NULL((void*)0);
4541 static GIcon *fallback_icon_preview = NULL((void*)0);
4542 if (fallback_icon == NULL((void*)0)) {

4544 fallback_icon_preview = g_themed_icon_new ("text-x-preview");
4545 g_themed_icon_append_name (G_THEMED_ICON (fallback_icon_preview)((((GThemedIcon*) (void *) ((fallback_icon_preview))))), "text-x-generic");
4546 }

4553
4554CajaIconInfo *
4555caja_file_get_icon (CajaFile *file,
4556 int size,
4557 int scale,
4558 CajaFileIconFlags flags)
4559{
4560 CajaIconInfo *icon;
4561 GIcon *gicon;
4562 GdkPixbuf *scaled_pixbuf;
4563
4564 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
4565 return NULL((void*)0);
4566 }
4567
4568 gicon = get_custom_icon (file);
4569 if (gicon) {
4570 GdkPixbuf *pixbuf;
4571
4572 icon = caja_icon_info_lookup (gicon, size, scale);
4573 g_object_unref (gicon);
4574
4575 pixbuf = caja_icon_info_get_pixbuf (icon);
4576 if (pixbuf != NULL((void*)0)) {
4577 if (!file->details->is_launcher && !gdk_pixbuf_get_has_alpha (pixbuf)) {
4578 caja_ui_frame_image (&pixbuf);
4579 }
4580 g_object_unref (icon);
4581
4582 icon = caja_icon_info_new_for_pixbuf (pixbuf, scale);
4583 g_object_unref (pixbuf);
4584 }
4585
4586 return icon;
4587 }
4588
4589 if (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_THUMBNAILS &&
4590 caja_file_should_show_thumbnail (file)) {
4591 int modified_size;
4592
4593 if (flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_FORCE_THUMBNAIL_SIZE) {
4594 modified_size = size * scale;
4595 } else {
4596 modified_size = size * scale * cached_thumbnail_size / CAJA_ICON_SIZE_STANDARD48;
4597 }
4598
4599 if (file->details->thumbnail) {
4600 int w, h, s;
4601 double thumb_scale;
4602 GdkPixbuf *raw_pixbuf;
4603
4604 raw_pixbuf = g_object_ref (file->details->thumbnail)((__typeof__ (file->details->thumbnail)) (g_object_ref)
(file->details->thumbnail));
4605
4606 w = gdk_pixbuf_get_width (raw_pixbuf);
4607 h = gdk_pixbuf_get_height (raw_pixbuf);
4608
4609 s = MAX (w, h)(((w) > (h)) ? (w) : (h));
4610 /* Don't scale up small thumbnails in the standard view */
4611 if (s <= cached_thumbnail_size) {
4612 thumb_scale = (double)size / CAJA_ICON_SIZE_STANDARD48;
4613 }
4614 else {
4615 thumb_scale = (double)modified_size / s;
4616 }
4617 /* Make sure that icons don't get smaller than CAJA_ICON_SIZE_SMALLEST */
4618 if (s*thumb_scale <= CAJA_ICON_SIZE_SMALLEST16) {
4619 thumb_scale = (double) CAJA_ICON_SIZE_SMALLEST16 / s;
4620 }
4621
4622 scaled_pixbuf = gdk_pixbuf_scale_simple (raw_pixbuf,
4623 MAX (w * thumb_scale, 1)(((w * thumb_scale) > (1)) ? (w * thumb_scale) : (1)),
4624 MAX (h * thumb_scale, 1)(((h * thumb_scale) > (1)) ? (h * thumb_scale) : (1)),
4625 GDK_INTERP_BILINEAR);
4626
4627 /* Render frames only for thumbnails of non-image files
4628 and for images with no alpha channel. */
4629 gboolean is_image = file->details->mime_type &&
4630 (strncmp (file->details->mime_type, "image/", 6) == 0);
4631 if (!is_image || !gdk_pixbuf_get_has_alpha (raw_pixbuf)) {
4632 caja_ui_frame_image (&scaled_pixbuf);
4633 }
4634
4635 g_object_unref (raw_pixbuf);
4636
4637 /* Don't scale up if more than 25%, then read the original
4638 image instead. We don't want to compare to exactly 100%,
4639 since the zoom level 150% gives thumbnails at 144, which is
4640 ok to scale up from 128. */
4641 if (modified_size > 128 * 1.25 * scale &&
4642 !file->details->thumbnail_wants_original &&
4643 caja_can_thumbnail_internally (file)) {
4644 /* Invalidate if we resize upward */
4645 file->details->thumbnail_wants_original = TRUE(!(0));
4646 caja_file_invalidate_attributes (file, CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_THUMBNAIL);
4647 }
4648
4649 icon = caja_icon_info_new_for_pixbuf (scaled_pixbuf, scale);
4650 g_object_unref (scaled_pixbuf);
4651 return icon;
4652 } else if (file->details->thumbnail_path == NULL((void*)0) &&
4653 file->details->can_read &&
4654 !file->details->is_thumbnailing &&
4655 !file->details->thumbnailing_failed) {
4656 if (caja_can_thumbnail (file)) {
4657 caja_create_thumbnail (file);
4658 }
4659 }
4660 }
4661
4662 if (file->details->is_thumbnailing &&
4663 flags & CAJA_FILE_ICON_FLAGS_USE_THUMBNAILS)
4664 gicon = g_themed_icon_new (ICON_NAME_THUMBNAIL_LOADING"image-loading");
4665 else
4666 gicon = caja_file_get_gicon (file, flags);
4667
4668 if (gicon) {
4669 icon = caja_icon_info_lookup (gicon, size, scale);
4670 g_object_unref (gicon);
4671 return icon;
4672 } else {
4673 return caja_icon_info_lookup (get_default_file_icon (flags), size, scale);
4674 }
4675}
4676
4677cairo_surface_t *
4678caja_file_get_icon_surface (CajaFile *file,
4679 int size,
4680 gboolean force_size,
4681 int scale,
4682 CajaFileIconFlags flags)
4683{
4684 CajaIconInfo *info;
4685 cairo_surface_t *surface;
4686
4687 info = caja_file_get_icon (file, size, scale, flags);
4688 if (force_size) {
4689 surface = caja_icon_info_get_surface_at_size (info, size);
4690 } else {
4691 surface = caja_icon_info_get_surface (info);
4692 }
4693 g_object_unref (info);
4694
4695 return surface;
4696}

4757
4758static const char *TODAY_TIME_FORMATS [] = {
4759 /* Today, use special word.
4760 * strftime patterns preceeded with the widest
4761 * possible resulting string for that pattern.
4762 *
4763 * Note to localizers: You can look at man strftime
4764 * for details on the format, but you should only use
4765 * the specifiers from the C standard, not extensions.
4766 * These include "%" followed by one of
4767 * "aAbBcdHIjmMpSUwWxXyYZ". There are two extensions
4768 * in the Caja version of strftime that can be
4769 * used (and match GNU extensions). Putting a "-"
4770 * between the "%" and any numeric directive will turn
4771 * off zero padding, and putting a "_" there will use
4772 * space padding instead of zero padding.
4773 */
4774 N_("today at 00:00:00 PM")("today at 00:00:00 PM"),
4775 N_("today at %-I:%M:%S %p")("today at %-I:%M:%S %p"),
4776
4777 N_("today at 00:00 PM")("today at 00:00 PM"),
4778 N_("today at %-I:%M %p")("today at %-I:%M %p"),
4779
4780 N_("today, 00:00 PM")("today, 00:00 PM"),
4781 N_("today, %-I:%M %p")("today, %-I:%M %p"),
4782
4783 N_("today")("today"),
4784 N_("today")("today"),
4785
4786 NULL((void*)0)
4787};
4788
4789static const char *YESTERDAY_TIME_FORMATS [] = {
4790 /* Yesterday, use special word.
4791 * Note to localizers: Same issues as "today" string.
4792 */
4793 N_("yesterday at 00:00:00 PM")("yesterday at 00:00:00 PM"),
4794 N_("yesterday at %-I:%M:%S %p")("yesterday at %-I:%M:%S %p"),
4795

4837
4838static char *
4839caja_file_fit_date_as_string (CajaFile *file,
4840 CajaDateType date_type,
4841 int width,
4842 CajaWidthMeasureCallback measure_callback,
4843 CajaTruncateCallback truncate_callback,
4844 void *measure_context)
4845{
4846 time_t file_time_raw;
4847 const char **formats;
4848 const char *format;
4849 char *date_string;
4850 gchar *result = NULL((void*)0);
4851 int i;
4852 GDateTime *date_time, *today, *end_of_today;
4853 GTimeSpan file_date_age;
4854
4855 if (!caja_file_get_date (file, date_type, &file_time_raw)) {
4856 return NULL((void*)0);
4857 }
4858
4859 date_time = g_date_time_new_from_unix_local (file_time_raw);
4860
4861 if (date_format_pref == CAJA_DATE_FORMAT_LOCALE) {
4862 result = g_date_time_format (date_time, "%c");
4863 goto out;
4864 } else if (date_format_pref == CAJA_DATE_FORMAT_ISO) {
4865 result = g_date_time_format (date_time, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S");
4866 goto out;
4867 }
4868
4869 today = g_date_time_new_now_local ();
4870 end_of_today = g_date_time_add_full (today, 0, 0, 1,
4871 -1 * g_date_time_get_hour (today),
4872 -1 * g_date_time_get_minute (today),
4873 -1.0 * g_date_time_get_seconds (today));
4874 g_date_time_unref (today);
4875
4876 file_date_age = g_date_time_difference (end_of_today, date_time);
4877 g_date_time_unref (end_of_today);
4878
4879 /* Format varies depending on how old the date is. This minimizes
4880 * the length (and thus clutter & complication) of typical dates
4881 * while providing sufficient detail for recent dates to make
4882 * them maximally understandable at a glance. Keep all format
4883 * strings separate rather than combining bits & pieces for
4884 * internationalization's sake.
4885 */
4886
4887 if (file_date_age <= 0 || file_date_age > 2 * G_TIME_SPAN_DAY((86400000000L))) {
4888 formats = CURRENT_WEEK_TIME_FORMATS;
4889 } else if (file_date_age > G_TIME_SPAN_DAY((86400000000L))) {
4890 formats = YESTERDAY_TIME_FORMATS;
4891 } else {
4892 formats = TODAY_TIME_FORMATS;
4893 }
4894
4895 /* Find the date format that just fits the required width. Instead of measuring
4896 * the resulting string width directly, measure the width of a template that represents
4897 * the widest possible version of a date in a given format. This is done by using M, m
4898 * and 0 for the variable letters/digits respectively.
4899 */
4900 format = NULL((void*)0);
4901
4902 for (i = 0; ; i += 2) {
4903 const char *width_template;
4904
4905 width_template = (formats [i] ? _(formats [i])dcgettext (((void*)0), formats [i], 5) : NULL((void*)0));
4906 if (width_template == NULL((void*)0)) {
4907 /* no more formats left */
4908 g_assert (format != NULL)do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_645
; if (format != ((void*)0)) _g_boolean_var_645 = 1; else _g_boolean_var_645
= 0; _g_boolean_var_645; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c", 4908, ((const char*) (__func__
)), "format != NULL"); } while (0);
4909
4910 /* Can't fit even the shortest format -- return an ellipsized form in the
4911 * shortest format
4912 */
4913
4914 date_string = g_date_time_format (date_time, format);
4915
4916 if (truncate_callback == NULL((void*)0)) {
4917 result = date_string;
4918 break;
4919 }
4920
4921 result = (* truncate_callback) (date_string, width, measure_context);
4922 g_free (date_string);
4923 break;
4924 }
4925
4926 format = _(formats [i + 1])dcgettext (((void*)0), formats [i + 1], 5);
4927
4928 if (measure_callback == NULL((void*)0)) {
4929 /* don't care about fitting the width */
4930 break;
4931 }
4932
4933 if ((* measure_callback) (width_template, measure_context) <= width) {
4934 /* The template fits, this is the format we can fit. */
4935 break;
4936 }
4937 }
4938
4939 if (result == NULL((void*)0)) {
4940 result = g_date_time_format (date_time, format);
4941 }
4942
4943out:
4944 g_date_time_unref (date_time);
4945 return result;
4946}

4949 * caja_file_fit_modified_date_as_string:
4950 *
4951 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file modification date,
4952 * truncated to @width using the measuring and truncating callbacks.
4953 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
4954 * @width: The desired resulting string width.
4955 * @measure_callback: The callback used to measure the string width.

4975{

4989 caja_file_unref (orig_file);
4990
4991 return filename;
4992 }
4993
4994 return NULL((void*)0);

5031{

5033
5034 g_return_val_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file), FALSE)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_646
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance

= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_646
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_646 = 0; _g_boolean_var_646; }), 1)

5035
5036 use_preview = caja_file_get_filesystem_use_preview (file);

5040 return FALSE(0);
5041 } else {

); } while (0);
5051
5052 if (use_preview == G_FILESYSTEM_PREVIEW_TYPE_NEVER) {
5053 /* file system says to never preview anything */
5054 return FALSE(0);
5055 } else if (use_preview == G_FILESYSTEM_PREVIEW_TYPE_IF_LOCAL) {
5056 /* file system says we should treat file as if it's local */
5057 return TRUE(!(0));
5058 } else {
5059 /* only local files */
5060 return caja_file_is_local (file);

5242{

5244 file->details->deep_counts_status = CAJA_REQUEST_NOT_STARTED;

5247 caja_directory_async_state_changed (file->details->directory);
5248 }

5303static void
5304set_attributes_get_info_callback (GObject *source_object,
5305 GAsyncResult *res,
5306 gpointer callback_data)
5307{
5308 CajaFileOperation *op;
5309 GFileInfo *new_info;
5310 GError *error;
5311
5312 op = callback_data;
5313
5314 error = NULL((void*)0);
5315 new_info = g_file_query_info_finish (G_FILE (source_object)((((GFile*) (void *) ((source_object))))), res, &error);
5316 if (new_info != NULL((void*)0)) {
5317 if (caja_file_update_info (op->file, new_info)) {
5318 caja_file_changed (op->file);
5319 }
5320 g_object_unref (new_info);
5321 }
5322 caja_file_operation_complete (op, NULL((void*)0), error);
5323 if (error) {
5324 g_error_free (error);
5325 }
5326}

5347 CAJA_FILE_DEFAULT_ATTRIBUTES"standard::*,access::*,mountable::*,time::*,unix::*,owner::*,selinux::*,thumbnail::*,id::filesystem,trash::orig-path,trash::deletion-date,metadata::*",
