5380/**
5381 * caja_file_can_get_permissions:
5382 *
5383 * Check whether the permissions for a file are determinable.
5384 * This might not be the case for files on non-UNIX file systems.
5385 *
5386 * @file: The file in question.
5387 *
5388 * Return value: TRUE if the permissions are valid.
5389 */
5390gboolean
5391caja_file_can_get_permissions (CajaFile *file)
5392{
5393 return file->details->has_permissions;
5394}
5395
5396/**
5397 * caja_file_can_set_permissions:
5398 *
5399 * Check whether the current user is allowed to change
5400 * the permissions of a file.
5401 *
5402 * @file: The file in question.
5403 *
5404 * Return value: TRUE if the current user can change the
5405 * permissions of @file, FALSE otherwise. It's always possible
5406 * that when you actually try to do it, you will fail.
5407 */
5408gboolean
5409caja_file_can_set_permissions (CajaFile *file)
5410{
5411 uid_t user_id;
5412
5413 if (file->details->uid != -1 &&
5414 caja_file_is_local (file)) {
5415 /* Check the user. */
5416 user_id = geteuid();
5417
5418 /* Owner is allowed to set permissions. */
5419 if (user_id == (uid_t) file->details->uid) {
5420 return TRUE(!(0));
5421 }
5422
5423 /* Root is also allowed to set permissions. */
5424 if (user_id == 0) {
5425 return TRUE(!(0));
5426 }
5427
5428 /* Nobody else is allowed. */
5429 return FALSE(0);
5430 }
5431
5432 /* pretend to have full chmod rights when no info is available, relevant when
5433 * the FS can't provide ownership info, for instance for FTP */
5434 return TRUE(!(0));
5435}
5436
5437guint
5438caja_file_get_permissions (CajaFile *file)
5439{
5440 g_return_val_if_fail (caja_file_can_get_permissions (file), 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_653
; if (caja_file_can_get_permissions (file)) _g_boolean_var_653
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_653 = 0; _g_boolean_var_653; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "caja_file_can_get_permissions (file)");
return (0); } } while (0);
5441
5442 return file->details->permissions;
5443}
5444
5445/**
5446 * caja_file_set_permissions:
5447 *
5448 * Change a file's permissions. This should only be called if
5449 * caja_file_can_set_permissions returned TRUE.
5450 *
5451 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
5452 * @new_permissions: New permissions value. This is the whole
5453 * set of permissions, not a delta.
5454 **/
5455void
5456caja_file_set_permissions (CajaFile *file,
5457 guint32 new_permissions,
5458 CajaFileOperationCallback callback,
5459 gpointer callback_data)
5460{
5461 GFileInfo *info;
5462
5463 if (!caja_file_can_set_permissions (file)) {
5464 GError *error;
5465
5466 /* Claim that something changed even if the permission change failed.
5467 * This makes it easier for some clients who see the "reverting"
5468 * to the old permissions as "changing back".
5469 */
5470 caja_file_changed (file);
5471 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_PERMISSION_DENIED,
5472 _("Not allowed to set permissions")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Not allowed to set permissions", 5));
5473 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
5474 g_error_free (error);
5475 return;
5476 }
5477
5478 /* Test the permissions-haven't-changed case explicitly
5479 * because we don't want to send the file-changed signal if
5480 * nothing changed.
5481 */
5482 if (new_permissions == file->details->permissions) {
5483 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), callback_data);
5484 return;
5485 }
5486
5487 // Start UNDO-REDO
5488 if (!caja_undostack_manager_is_undo_redo(caja_undostack_manager_instance())) {
5489 CajaUndoStackActionData* undo_redo_data = caja_undostack_manager_data_new (CAJA_UNDOSTACK_SETPERMISSIONS, 1);
5490 caja_undostack_manager_data_set_file_permissions(undo_redo_data, caja_file_get_uri(file), file->details->permissions, new_permissions);
5491 caja_undostack_manager_add_action (caja_undostack_manager_instance(),
5492 undo_redo_data);
5493 }
5494 // End UNDO-REDO
5495
5496 info = g_file_info_new ();
5497 g_file_info_set_attribute_uint32 (info, G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_UNIX_MODE"unix::mode", new_permissions);
5498 caja_file_set_attributes (file, info, callback, callback_data);
5499 g_object_unref (info);
5500}

5507 * files without a context or systems that don't support selinux.

5530caja_file_get_selinux_context (CajaFile *file)
5531{

5534
5535 g_return_val_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file), NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_654
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_654
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_654 = 0; _g_boolean_var_654; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); return (((void*)
0)); } } while (0);
5536

5538 return NULL((void*)0);
5539 }
5540

5542
5543#ifdef HAVE_SELINUX1

5558
5559static char *
5560get_real_name (const char *name, const char *gecos)
5561{
5562 char *locale_string, *part_before_comma, *capitalized_login_name, *real_name;
5563
5564 if (gecos == NULL((void*)0)) {
5565 return NULL((void*)0);
5566 }
5567
5568 locale_string = eel_str_strip_substring_and_after (gecos, ",");
5569 if (!g_utf8_validate (locale_string, -1, NULL((void*)0))) {
5570 part_before_comma = g_locale_to_utf8 (locale_string, -1, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
5571 g_free (locale_string);
5572 } else {
5573 part_before_comma = locale_string;
5574 }
5575
5576 if (!g_utf8_validate (name, -1, NULL((void*)0))) {
5577 locale_string = g_locale_to_utf8 (name, -1, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
5578 } else {
5579 locale_string = g_strdup (name)g_strdup_inline (name);
5580 }
5581
5582 capitalized_login_name = eel_str_capitalize (locale_string);
5583 g_free (locale_string);
5584
5585 if (capitalized_login_name == NULL((void*)0)) {
5586 real_name = part_before_comma;
5587 } else {
5588 real_name = eel_str_replace_substring
5589 (part_before_comma, "&", capitalized_login_name);
5590 g_free (part_before_comma);
5591 }
5592
5593 if (eel_str_is_empty (real_name)
5594 || eel_strcmp (name, real_name) == 0
5595 || eel_strcmp (capitalized_login_name, real_name) == 0) {
5596 g_free (real_name);
5597 real_name = NULL((void*)0);
5598 }
5599
5600 g_free (capitalized_login_name);
5601
5602 return real_name;
5603}

5681gboolean
5682caja_file_can_get_owner (CajaFile *file)
5683{

5685 return file->details->uid != -1;
5686}

5689 * caja_file_get_owner_name:
5690 *
5691 * Get the user name of the file's owner. If the owner has no

5694 *

5704
5705/**
5706 * caja_file_can_set_owner:
5707 *
5708 * Check whether the current user is allowed to change
5709 * the owner of a file.
5710 *
5711 * @file: The file in question.
5712 *
5713 * Return value: TRUE if the current user can change the
5714 * owner of @file, FALSE otherwise. It's always possible
5715 * that when you actually try to do it, you will fail.
5716 */
5717gboolean
5718caja_file_can_set_owner (CajaFile *file)
5719{
5720 /* Not allowed to set the owner if we can't
5721 * even read it. This can happen on non-UNIX file
5722 * systems.
5723 */
5724 if (!caja_file_can_get_owner (file)) {
5725 return FALSE(0);
5726 }
5727
5728 /* Only root is also allowed to set the owner. */
5729 return geteuid() == 0;
5730}
5731
5732/**
5733 * caja_file_set_owner:
5734 *
5735 * Set the owner of a file. This will only have any effect if
5736 * caja_file_can_set_owner returns TRUE.
5737 *
5738 * @file: The file in question.
5739 * @user_name_or_id: The user name to set the owner to.
5740 * If the string does not match any user name, and the
5741 * string is an integer, the owner will be set to the
5742 * userid represented by that integer.
5743 * @callback: Function called when asynch owner change succeeds or fails.
5744 * @callback_data: Parameter passed back with callback function.
5745 */
5746void
5747caja_file_set_owner (CajaFile *file,
5748 const char *user_name_or_id,
5749 CajaFileOperationCallback callback,
5750 gpointer callback_data)
5751{
5752 GError *error;
5753 GFileInfo *info;
5754 uid_t new_id;
5755
5756 if (!caja_file_can_set_owner (file)) {
5757 /* Claim that something changed even if the permission
5758 * change failed. This makes it easier for some
5759 * clients who see the "reverting" to the old owner as
5760 * "changing back".
5761 */
5762 caja_file_changed (file);
5763 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_PERMISSION_DENIED,
5764 _("Not allowed to set owner")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Not allowed to set owner", 5));
5765 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
5766 g_error_free (error);
5767 return;
5768 }
5769
5770 /* If no match treating user_name_or_id as name, try treating
5771 * it as id.
5772 */
5773 if (!get_user_id_from_user_name (user_name_or_id, &new_id)
5774 && !get_id_from_digit_string (user_name_or_id, &new_id)) {
5775 /* Claim that something changed even if the permission
5776 * change failed. This makes it easier for some
5777 * clients who see the "reverting" to the old owner as
5778 * "changing back".
5779 */
5780 caja_file_changed (file);
5781 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT,
5782 _("Specified owner '%s' doesn't exist")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Specified owner '%s' doesn't exist", 5
), user_name_or_id);
5783 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
5784 g_error_free (error);
5785 return;
5786 }
5787
5788 /* Test the owner-hasn't-changed case explicitly because we
5789 * don't want to send the file-changed signal if nothing
5790 * changed.
5791 */
5792 if (new_id == (uid_t) file->details->uid) {
5793 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), callback_data);
5794 return;
5795 }
5796
5797 // Start UNDO-REDO
5798 if (!caja_undostack_manager_is_undo_redo(caja_undostack_manager_instance())) {
5799 char* current_owner = caja_file_get_owner_as_string (file, FALSE(0));
5800 CajaUndoStackActionData* undo_redo_data = caja_undostack_manager_data_new (CAJA_UNDOSTACK_CHANGEOWNER, 1);
5801 caja_undostack_manager_data_set_owner_change_information(undo_redo_data, caja_file_get_uri(file), current_owner, user_name_or_id);
5802 caja_undostack_manager_add_action (caja_undostack_manager_instance(),
5803 undo_redo_data);
5804 g_free(current_owner);
5805 }
5806 // End UNDO-REDO
5807
5808 info = g_file_info_new ();
5809 g_file_info_set_attribute_uint32 (info, G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_UNIX_UID"unix::uid", new_id);
5810 caja_file_set_attributes (file, info, callback, callback_data);
5811 g_object_unref (info);
5812}
5813
5814/**
5815 * caja_get_user_names:
5816 *
5817 * Get a list of user names. For users with a different associated
5818 * "real name", the real name follows the standard user name, separated
5819 * by a carriage return. The caller is responsible for freeing this list
5820 * and its contents.
5821 */
5822GList *
5823caja_get_user_names (void)
5824{
5825 GList *list;
5826 char *name;
5827 struct passwd *user;
5828
5829 list = NULL((void*)0);
5830
5831 setpwent ();
5832
5833 while ((user = getpwent ()) != NULL((void*)0)) {
5834 char *real_name;
5835
5836 real_name = get_real_name (user->pw_name, user->pw_gecos);
5837 if (real_name != NULL((void*)0)) {
5838 name = g_strconcat (user->pw_name, "\n", real_name, NULL((void*)0));
5839 } else {
5840 name = g_strdup (user->pw_name)g_strdup_inline (user->pw_name);
5841 }
5842 g_free (real_name);
5843 list = g_list_prepend (list, name);
5844 }
5845
5846 endpwent ();
5847
5848 return eel_g_str_list_alphabetize (list);
5849}

5851/**
5852 * caja_file_can_get_group:
5853 *
5854 * Check whether the group a file is determinable.
5855 * This might not be the case for files on non-UNIX file systems.
5856 *
5857 * @file: The file in question.
5858 *
5859 * Return value: TRUE if the group is valid.
5860 */
5861gboolean
5862caja_file_can_get_group (CajaFile *file)
5863{
5864 /* Before we have info on a file, the group is unknown. */
5865 return file->details->gid != -1;
5866}
5867
5868/**
5869 * caja_file_get_group_name:
5870 *
5871 * Get the name of the file's group. If the group has no
5872 * name, returns the groupid as a string. The caller is responsible
5873 * for g_free-ing this string.
5874 *
5875 * @file: The file in question.
5876 *
5877 * Return value: A newly-allocated string.
5878 **/
5879char *
5880caja_file_get_group_name (CajaFile *file)
5881{
5882 return g_strdup (file->details->group)g_strdup_inline (file->details->group);
5883}
5884
5885/**
5886 * caja_file_can_set_group:
5887 *
5888 * Check whether the current user is allowed to change
5889 * the group of a file.
5890 *
5891 * @file: The file in question.
5892 *
5893 * Return value: TRUE if the current user can change the
5894 * group of @file, FALSE otherwise. It's always possible
5895 * that when you actually try to do it, you will fail.
5896 */
5897gboolean
5898caja_file_can_set_group (CajaFile *file)
5899{
5900 uid_t user_id;
5901
5902 /* Not allowed to set the permissions if we can't
5903 * even read them. This can happen on non-UNIX file
5904 * systems.
5905 */
5906 if (!caja_file_can_get_group (file)) {
5907 return FALSE(0);
5908 }
5909
5910 /* Check the user. */
5911 user_id = geteuid();
5912
5913 /* Owner is allowed to set group (with restrictions). */
5914 if (user_id == (uid_t) file->details->uid) {
5915 return TRUE(!(0));
5916 }
5917
5918 /* Root is also allowed to set group. */
5919 if (user_id == 0) {
5920 return TRUE(!(0));
5921 }
5922
5923 /* Nobody else is allowed. */
5924 return FALSE(0);
5925}
5926
5927/* Get a list of group names, filtered to only the ones
5928 * that contain the given username. If the username is
5929 * NULL, returns a list of all group names.
5930 */
5931static GList *
5932caja_get_group_names_for_user (void)
5933{
5934 GList *list;
5935 int count, i;
5936 gid_t gid_list[NGROUPS_MAX65536 + 1];
5937 struct group *group = NULL((void*)0);
5938
5939 list = NULL((void*)0);
5940
5941 count = getgroups (NGROUPS_MAX65536 + 1, gid_list);
5942 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
5943 group = getgrgid (gid_list[i]);
5944 if (group == NULL((void*)0))
5945 break;
5946
5947 list = g_list_prepend (list, g_strdup (group->gr_name)g_strdup_inline (group->gr_name));
5948 }
5949
5950 return eel_g_str_list_alphabetize (list);
5951}
5952
5953/**
5954 * caja_get_group_names:
5955 *
5956 * Get a list of all group names.
5957 */
5958GList *
5959caja_get_all_group_names (void)
5960{
5961 GList *list;
5962 struct group *group;
5963
5964 list = NULL((void*)0);
5965
5966 setgrent ();
5967
5968 while ((group = getgrent ()) != NULL((void*)0))
5969 list = g_list_prepend (list, g_strdup (group->gr_name)g_strdup_inline (group->gr_name));
5970
5971 endgrent ();
5972
5973 return eel_g_str_list_alphabetize (list);
5974}
5975
5976/**
5977 * caja_file_get_settable_group_names:
5978 *
5979 * Get a list of all group names that the current user
5980 * can set the group of a specific file to.
5981 *
5982 * @file: The CajaFile in question.
5983 */
5984GList *
5985caja_file_get_settable_group_names (CajaFile *file)
5986{
5987 uid_t user_id;
5988 GList *result;
5989
5990 if (!caja_file_can_set_group (file)) {
5991 return NULL((void*)0);
5992 }
5993
5994 /* Check the user. */
5995 user_id = geteuid();
5996
5997 if (user_id == 0) {
5998 /* Root is allowed to set group to anything. */
5999 result = caja_get_all_group_names ();
6000 } else if (user_id == (uid_t) file->details->uid) {
6001 /* Owner is allowed to set group to any that owner is member of. */
6002 result = caja_get_group_names_for_user ();
6003 } else {
6004 g_warning ("unhandled case in caja_get_settable_group_names");
6005 result = NULL((void*)0);
6006 }
6007
6008 return result;
6009}
6010
6011/**
6012 * caja_file_set_group:
6013 *
6014 * Set the group of a file. This will only have any effect if
6015 * caja_file_can_set_group returns TRUE.
6016 *
6017 * @file: The file in question.
6018 * @group_name_or_id: The group name to set the owner to.
6019 * If the string does not match any group name, and the
6020 * string is an integer, the group will be set to the
6021 * group id represented by that integer.
6022 * @callback: Function called when asynch group change succeeds or fails.
6023 * @callback_data: Parameter passed back with callback function.
6024 */
6025void
6026caja_file_set_group (CajaFile *file,
6027 const char *group_name_or_id,
6028 CajaFileOperationCallback callback,
6029 gpointer callback_data)
6030{
6031 GError *error;
6032 GFileInfo *info;
6033 uid_t new_id;
6034
6035 if (!caja_file_can_set_group (file)) {
6036 /* Claim that something changed even if the group
6037 * change failed. This makes it easier for some
6038 * clients who see the "reverting" to the old group as
6039 * "changing back".
6040 */
6041 caja_file_changed (file);
6042 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_PERMISSION_DENIED,
6043 _("Not allowed to set group")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Not allowed to set group", 5));
6044 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
6045 g_error_free (error);
6046 return;
6047 }
6048
6049 /* If no match treating group_name_or_id as name, try treating
6050 * it as id.
6051 */
6052 if (!get_group_id_from_group_name (group_name_or_id, &new_id)
6053 && !get_id_from_digit_string (group_name_or_id, &new_id)) {
6054 /* Claim that something changed even if the group
6055 * change failed. This makes it easier for some
6056 * clients who see the "reverting" to the old group as
6057 * "changing back".
6058 */
6059 caja_file_changed (file);
6060 error = g_error_new (G_IO_ERRORg_io_error_quark(), G_IO_ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT,
6061 _("Specified group '%s' doesn't exist")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Specified group '%s' doesn't exist", 5
), group_name_or_id);
6062 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), error, callback_data);
6063 g_error_free (error);
6064 return;
6065 }
6066
6067 if (new_id == (gid_t) file->details->gid) {
6068 (* callback) (file, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), callback_data);
6069 return;
6070 }
6071
6072 // Start UNDO-REDO
6073 if (!caja_undostack_manager_is_undo_redo(caja_undostack_manager_instance())) {
6074 char* current_group = caja_file_get_group_name (file);
6075 CajaUndoStackActionData* undo_redo_data = caja_undostack_manager_data_new (CAJA_UNDOSTACK_CHANGEGROUP, 1);
6076 caja_undostack_manager_data_set_group_change_information(undo_redo_data, caja_file_get_uri(file), current_group, group_name_or_id);
6077 caja_undostack_manager_add_action (caja_undostack_manager_instance(),
6078 undo_redo_data);
6079 g_free(current_group);
6080 }
6081 // End UNDO-REDO
6082
6083 info = g_file_info_new ();
6084 g_file_info_set_attribute_uint32 (info, G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_UNIX_GID"unix::gid", new_id);
6085 caja_file_set_attributes (file, info, callback, callback_data);
6086 g_object_unref (info);
6087}

6092 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file's permissions

6101caja_file_get_octal_permissions_as_string (CajaFile *file)
6102{
6103 guint32 permissions;
6104
6105 g_assert (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_658
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_658
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_658 = 0; _g_boolean_var_658; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"

6115/**
6116 * caja_file_get_permissions_as_string:
6117 *
6118 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file's permissions. The caller
6119 * is responsible for g_free-ing this string.
6120 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
6121 *
6122 * Returns: Newly allocated string ready to display to the user.
6123 *
6124 **/
6125static char *
6126caja_file_get_permissions_as_string (CajaFile *file)
6127{
6128 guint32 permissions;
6129 gboolean is_directory;
6130 gboolean is_link;
6131 gboolean suid, sgid, sticky;
6132
6133 if (!caja_file_can_get_permissions (file)) {
6134 return NULL((void*)0);
6135 }
6136
6137 g_assert (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_659
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_659
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_659 = 0; _g_boolean_var_659; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 6137, ((const char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); }
while (0);
6138
6139 permissions = file->details->permissions;
6140 is_directory = caja_file_is_directory (file);
6141 is_link = caja_file_is_symbolic_link (file);
6142
6143 /* We use ls conventions for displaying these three obscure flags */
6144 suid = permissions & S_ISUID04000;
6145 sgid = permissions & S_ISGID02000;
6146 sticky = permissions & S_ISVTX01000;
6147
6148 return g_strdup_printf ("%c%c%c%c%c%c%c%c%c%c",
6149 is_link ? 'l' : is_directory ? 'd' : '-',
6150 permissions & S_IRUSR0400 ? 'r' : '-',
6151 permissions & S_IWUSR0200 ? 'w' : '-',
6152 permissions & S_IXUSR0100
6153 ? (suid ? 's' : 'x')
6154 : (suid ? 'S' : '-'),
6155 permissions & S_IRGRP(0400 >> 3) ? 'r' : '-',
6156 permissions & S_IWGRP(0200 >> 3) ? 'w' : '-',
6157 permissions & S_IXGRP(0100 >> 3)
6158 ? (sgid ? 's' : 'x')
6159 : (sgid ? 'S' : '-'),
6160 permissions & S_IROTH((0400 >> 3) >> 3) ? 'r' : '-',
6161 permissions & S_IWOTH((0200 >> 3) >> 3) ? 'w' : '-',
6162 permissions & S_IXOTH((0100 >> 3) >> 3)
6163 ? (sticky ? 't' : 'x')
6164 : (sticky ? 'T' : '-'));
6165}

6167/**
6168 * caja_file_get_owner_as_string:
6169 *
6170 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file's owner. The caller
6171 * is responsible for g_free-ing this string.
6172 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
6173 * @include_real_name: Whether or not to append the real name (if any)
6174 * for this user after the user name.
6175 *
6176 * Returns: Newly allocated string ready to display to the user.
6177 *
6178 **/
6179static char *
6180caja_file_get_owner_as_string (CajaFile *file, gboolean include_real_name)
6181{
6182 char *user_name;
6183
6184 /* Before we have info on a file, the owner is unknown. */
6185 if (file->details->owner == NULL((void*)0) &&
6186 file->details->owner_real == NULL((void*)0)) {
6187 return NULL((void*)0);
6188 }
6189
6190 if (file->details->owner_real == NULL((void*)0)) {
6191 user_name = g_strdup (file->details->owner)g_strdup_inline (file->details->owner);
6192 } else if (file->details->owner == NULL((void*)0)) {
6193 user_name = g_strdup (file->details->owner_real)g_strdup_inline (file->details->owner_real);
6194 } else if (include_real_name &&
6195 strcmp (file->details->owner, file->details->owner_real) != 0) {
6196 user_name = g_strdup_printf ("%s - %s",
6197 file->details->owner,
6198 file->details->owner_real);
6199 } else {
6200 user_name = g_strdup (file->details->owner)g_strdup_inline (file->details->owner);
6201 }
6202
6203 return user_name;
6204}

; if (includes_directories || includes_files) _g_boolean_var_660
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_660 = 0; _g_boolean_var_660; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 6211, ((const char*) (__func__)), "includes_directories || includes_files"

6212
6213 return g_strdup_printf (includes_directories
6214 ? (includes_files
6215 ? ngettext ("%'u item", "%'u items", item_count)dcngettext (((void*)0), "%'u item", "%'u items", item_count, 5

), item_count);

6220/**
6221 * caja_file_get_size_as_string:
6222 *
6223 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file size. The caller
6224 * is responsible for g_free-ing this string. The string is an item
6225 * count for directories.
6226 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
6227 * @size_on_disk: If TRUE will return the size on disk. If FALSE return file size.
6228 *
6229 * Returns: Newly allocated string ready to display to the user.
6230 *
6231 **/
6232static char *
6233caja_file_get_size_as_string (CajaFile *file,
6234 gboolean size_on_disk)
6235{
6236 guint item_count;
6237 gboolean count_unreadable;
6238 goffset size;
6239
6240 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
6241 return NULL((void*)0);
6242 }
6243
6244 g_assert (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_661
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_661
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_661 = 0; _g_boolean_var_661; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 6244, ((const char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); }
while (0);
6245
6246 if (caja_file_is_directory (file)) {
6247 if (!caja_file_get_directory_item_count (file, &item_count, &count_unreadable)) {
6248 return NULL((void*)0);
6249 }
6250 return format_item_count_for_display (item_count, TRUE(!(0)), TRUE(!(0)));
6251 }
6252
6253 if (size_on_disk) {
6254 size = file->details->size_on_disk;
6255 } else {
6256 size = file->details->size;
6257 }
6258

6260 return NULL((void*)0);
6261 }

6263 if (g_settings_get_boolean (caja_preferences, CAJA_PREFERENCES_USE_IEC_UNITS"use-iec-units"))
6264 return g_format_size_full ((guint64) size, G_FORMAT_SIZE_IEC_UNITS);
6265 else
6266 return g_format_size ((guint64) size);
6267}

6269/**
6270 * caja_file_get_size_as_string_with_real_size:
6271 *
6272 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file size. The caller
6273 * is responsible for g_free-ing this string. The string is an item
6274 * count for directories.
6275 * This function adds the real size in the string.
6276 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
6277 *
6278 * Returns: Newly allocated string ready to display to the user.
6279 *
6280 **/
6281static char *
6282caja_file_get_size_as_string_with_real_size (CajaFile *file,
6283 gboolean size_on_disk)
6284{
6285 guint item_count;
6286 gboolean count_unreadable;
6287 goffset size;
6288 char * formatted;
6289 char * formatted_plus_real;
6290 char * real_size;
6291
6292 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
6293 return NULL((void*)0);
6294 }
6295
6296 g_assert (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_662
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_662
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_662 = 0; _g_boolean_var_662; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 6296, ((const char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); }
while (0);
6297
6298 if (caja_file_is_directory (file)) {
6299 if (!caja_file_get_directory_item_count (file, &item_count, &count_unreadable)) {
6300 return NULL((void*)0);
6301 }
6302 return format_item_count_for_display (item_count, TRUE(!(0)), TRUE(!(0)));
6303 }
6304
6305 if (size_on_disk) {
6306 size = file->details->size_on_disk;
6307 } else {
6308 size = file->details->size;
6309 }
6310
6311 if (size == -1) {
6312 return NULL((void*)0);
6313 }
6314
6315 if (g_settings_get_boolean (caja_preferences, CAJA_PREFERENCES_USE_IEC_UNITS"use-iec-units"))
6316 formatted = g_format_size_full (size, G_FORMAT_SIZE_IEC_UNITS);
6317 else
6318 formatted = g_format_size(size);
6319
6320 /* Do this in a separate stage so that we don't have to put G_GUINT64_FORMAT in the translated string */

6740 attribute_q == attribute_trashed_on_q ||
6741 attribute_q == attribute_date_permissions_q) {
6742 return TRUE(!(0));
6743 }
6744
6745 return FALSE(0);
6746}

6748/**
6749 * get_description:
6750 *
6751 * Get a user-displayable string representing a file type. The caller
6752 * is responsible for g_free-ing this string.
6753 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
6754 *
6755 * Returns: Newly allocated string ready to display to the user.
6756 *
6757 **/
6758static char *
6759get_description (CajaFile *file)
6760{
6761 const char *mime_type;
6762 char *description;
6763
6764 g_assert (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_669
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_669
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_669 = 0; _g_boolean_var_669; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 6764, ((const char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); }
while (0);
6765
6766 mime_type = file->details->mime_type;
6767 if (eel_str_is_empty (mime_type)) {
6768 return NULL((void*)0);
6769 }
6770
6771 if (g_content_type_is_unknown (mime_type) &&
6772 caja_file_is_executable (file)) {
6773 return g_strdup (_("program"))g_strdup_inline (dcgettext (((void*)0), "program", 5));
6774 }
6775
6776 description = g_content_type_get_description (mime_type);
6777 if (!eel_str_is_empty (description)) {
6778 return description;
6779 }
6780
6781 return g_strdup (mime_type)g_strdup_inline (mime_type);
6782}

6784/* Takes ownership of string */
6785static char *
6786update_description_for_link (CajaFile *file, char *string)
6787{
6788 if (caja_file_is_symbolic_link (file)) {
6789 char *res;
6790
6791 g_assert (!caja_file_is_broken_symbolic_link (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_670
; if (!caja_file_is_broken_symbolic_link (file)) _g_boolean_var_670
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_670 = 0; _g_boolean_var_670; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 6791, ((const char*) (__func__)), "!caja_file_is_broken_symbolic_link (file)"
); } while (0);
6792 if (string == NULL((void*)0)) {
6793 return g_strdup (_("link"))g_strdup_inline (dcgettext (((void*)0), "link", 5));
6794 }
6795 /* Note to localizers: convert file type string for file
6796 * (e.g. "folder", "plain text") to file type for symbolic link
6797 * to that kind of file (e.g. "link to folder").
6798 */
6799 res = g_strdup_printf (_("Link to %s")dcgettext (((void*)0), "Link to %s", 5), string);

6802 }

6904/**
6905 * caja_file_get_emblem_icons
6906 *
6907 * Return the list of names of emblems that this file should display,
6908 * in canonical order.
6909 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
6910 *
6911 * Returns: A list of emblem names.
6912 *
6913 **/
6914GList *
6915caja_file_get_emblem_icons (CajaFile *file,
6916 char **exclude)
6917{
6918 GList *keywords, *l;
6919 GList *icons;
6920 char *icon_names[2];
6921 char *keyword;
6922 int i;
6923 GIcon *icon;
6924
6925 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
6926 return NULL((void*)0);
6927 }
6928
6929 g_return_val_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file), NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_674
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_674
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_674 = 0; _g_boolean_var_674; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); return (((void*)
0)); } } while (0);
6930
6931 keywords = caja_file_get_keywords (file);
6932 keywords = prepend_automatic_keywords (file, keywords);
6933
6934 icons = NULL((void*)0);
6935 for (l = keywords; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
6936 keyword = l->data;
6937
6938#ifdef TRASH_IS_FAST_ENOUGH
6939 if (strcmp (keyword, CAJA_FILE_EMBLEM_NAME_TRASH"trash") == 0) {
6940 char *uri;
6941 gboolean file_is_trash;
6942 /* Leave out the trash emblem for the trash itself, since
6943 * putting a trash emblem on a trash icon is gilding the
6944 * lily.
6945 */
6946 uri = caja_file_get_uri (file);
6947 file_is_trash = strcmp (uri, EEL_TRASH_URI"trash:") == 0;
6948 g_free (uri);
6949 if (file_is_trash) {
6950 continue;
6951 }
6952 }
6953#endif
6954 if (exclude) {
6955 for (i = 0; exclude[i] != NULL((void*)0); i++) {
6956 if (strcmp (exclude[i], keyword) == 0) {
6957 continue;
6958 }
6959 }
6960 }
6961
6962 icon_names[0] = g_strconcat ("emblem-", keyword, NULL((void*)0));
6963 icon_names[1] = keyword;
6964 icon = g_themed_icon_new_from_names (icon_names, 2);
6965 g_free (icon_names[0]);
6966
6967 icons = g_list_prepend (icons, icon);
6968 }
6969
6970 g_list_free_full (keywords, g_free);
6971
6972 return icons;
6973}

6975GList *
6976caja_file_get_emblem_pixbufs (CajaFile *file,
6977 int size,
6978 gboolean force_size,
6979 char **exclude)
6980{
6981 GList *icons, *l;
6982 GList *pixbufs;
6983 GdkPixbuf *pixbuf;
6984 GIcon *icon = NULL((void*)0);
6985 CajaIconInfo *icon_info = NULL((void*)0);
6986
6987 icons = caja_file_get_emblem_icons (file, exclude);
6988 pixbufs = NULL((void*)0);
6989
6990 for (l = icons; l != NULL((void*)0); l = l->next) {
6991 icon = l->data;
6992
6993 icon_info = caja_icon_info_lookup (icon, size, 1);
6994 if (force_size) {
6995 pixbuf = caja_icon_info_get_pixbuf_nodefault_at_size (icon_info, size);
6996 } else {
6997 pixbuf = caja_icon_info_get_pixbuf_nodefault (icon_info);
6998 }
6999
7000 if (pixbuf) {
7001 pixbufs = g_list_prepend (pixbufs, pixbuf);
7002 }
7003
7004 g_object_unref (icon_info);
7005 g_object_unref (icon);
7006 }
7007 g_list_free (icons);
7008
7009 return g_list_reverse (pixbufs);
7010
7011}
7012
7013static GList *
7014sort_keyword_list_and_remove_duplicates (GList *keywords)
7015{
7016 GList *p;
7017
7018 if (keywords != NULL((void*)0)) {
7019 GList *duplicate_link = NULL((void*)0);
7020
7021 keywords = eel_g_str_list_alphabetize (keywords);
7022
7023 p = keywords;
7024 while (p->next != NULL((void*)0)) {
7025 if (strcmp ((const char *) p->data, (const char *) p->next->data) == 0) {
7026 duplicate_link = p->next;
7027 keywords = g_list_remove_link (keywords, duplicate_link);
7028 g_list_free_full (duplicate_link, g_free);
7029 } else {
7030 p = p->next;
7031 }
7032 }
7033 }
7034
7035 return keywords;
7036}

7173
7174static void
7175get_fs_free_cb (GObject *source_object,
7176 GAsyncResult *res,
7177 gpointer user_data)
7178{
7179 CajaDirectory *directory;
7180 guint64 free_space;
7181 GFileInfo *info;
7182
7183 directory = CAJA_DIRECTORY (user_data)((((CajaDirectory*) (void *) ((user_data)))));
7184
7185 free_space = (guint64)-1;
7186 info = g_file_query_filesystem_info_finish (G_FILE (source_object)((((GFile*) (void *) ((source_object))))),
7187 res, NULL((void*)0));
7188 if (info) {
7189 if (g_file_info_has_attribute (info, G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_FILESYSTEM_FREE"filesystem::free")) {
7190 free_space = g_file_info_get_attribute_uint64 (info, G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_FILESYSTEM_FREE"filesystem::free");
7191 }
7192 g_object_unref (info);
7193 }
7194
7195 if (directory->details->free_space != free_space) {
7196 CajaFile *file;
7197
7198 directory->details->free_space = free_space;
7199 file = caja_directory_get_existing_corresponding_file (directory);
7200 if (file) {
7201 caja_file_emit_changed (file);
7202 caja_file_unref (file);
7203 }
7204 }
7205 caja_directory_unref (directory);
7206}
7207
7208/**
7209 * caja_file_get_volume_free_space
7210 * Get a nicely formatted char with free space on the file's volume
7211 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
7212 *
7213 * Returns: newly-allocated copy of file size in a formatted string
7214 */
7215char *
7216caja_file_get_volume_free_space (CajaFile *file)
7217{
7218 CajaDirectory *directory;
7219 char *res;
7220 time_t now;
7221
7222 directory = caja_directory_get_for_file (file);
7223
7224 now = time (NULL((void*)0));
7225 /* Update first time and then every 2 seconds */
7226 if (directory->details->free_space_read == 0 ||
7227 (now - directory->details->free_space_read) > 2) {
7228 GFile *location;
7229
7230 directory->details->free_space_read = now;
7231 location = caja_file_get_location (file);
7232 g_file_query_filesystem_info_async (location,
7233 G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_FILESYSTEM_FREE"filesystem::free",
7234 0, NULL((void*)0),
7235 get_fs_free_cb,
7236 directory); /* Inherits ref */
7237 g_object_unref (location);
7238 } else {
7239 caja_directory_unref (directory);
7240 }
7241
7242 res = NULL((void*)0);
7243
7244 if (directory->details->free_space != (guint64) -1)
7245 {
7246 if (g_settings_get_boolean (caja_preferences, CAJA_PREFERENCES_USE_IEC_UNITS"use-iec-units"))
7247 res = g_format_size_full (directory->details->free_space, G_FORMAT_SIZE_IEC_UNITS);
7248 else
7249 res = g_format_size(directory->details->free_space);
7250 }
7251
7252 return res;
7253}
7254
7255/**
7256 * caja_file_get_volume_name
7257 * Get the path of the volume the file resides on
7258 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
7259 *
7260 * Returns: newly-allocated copy of the volume name of the target file,
7261 * if the volume name isn't set, it returns the mount path of the volume
7262 */
7263char *
7264caja_file_get_volume_name (CajaFile *file)
7265{
7266 GFile *location;
7267 char *res;
7268 GMount *mount;
7269
7270 res = NULL((void*)0);
7271
7272 location = caja_file_get_location (file);
7273 mount = g_file_find_enclosing_mount (location, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
7274 if (mount) {
7275 res = g_strdup (g_mount_get_name (mount))g_strdup_inline (g_mount_get_name (mount));
7276 g_object_unref (mount);
7277 }
7278 g_object_unref (location);
7279
7280 return res;
7281}

7283/**
7284 * caja_file_get_symbolic_link_target_path
7285 *
7286 * Get the file path of the target of a symbolic link. It is an error
7287 * to call this function on a file that isn't a symbolic link.
7288 * @file: CajaFile representing the symbolic link in question.
7289 *
7290 * Returns: newly-allocated copy of the file path of the target of the symbolic link.
7291 */
7292char *
7293caja_file_get_symbolic_link_target_path (CajaFile *file)
7294{
7295 if (!caja_file_is_symbolic_link (file)) {
7296 g_warning ("File has symlink target, but is not marked as symlink");
7297 }
7298
7299 return g_strdup (file->details->symlink_name)g_strdup_inline (file->details->symlink_name);
7300}
7301
7302/**
7303 * caja_file_get_symbolic_link_target_uri
7304 *
7305 * Get the uri of the target of a symbolic link. It is an error
7306 * to call this function on a file that isn't a symbolic link.
7307 * @file: CajaFile representing the symbolic link in question.
7308 *
7309 * Returns: newly-allocated copy of the uri of the target of the symbolic link.
7310 */
7311char *
7312caja_file_get_symbolic_link_target_uri (CajaFile *file)
7313{
7314 if (!caja_file_is_symbolic_link (file)) {
7315 g_warning ("File has symlink target, but is not marked as symlink");
7316 }
7317
7318 if (file->details->symlink_name == NULL((void*)0)) {
7319 return NULL((void*)0);
7320 } else {
7321 GFile *location, *parent, *target;
7322 char *target_uri;
7323
7324 target = NULL((void*)0);
7325
7326 location = caja_file_get_location (file);
7327 parent = g_file_get_parent (location);
7328 g_object_unref (location);
7329 if (parent) {
7330 target = g_file_resolve_relative_path (parent, file->details->symlink_name);
7331 g_object_unref (parent);
7332 }
7333
7334 target_uri = NULL((void*)0);
7335 if (target) {
7336 target_uri = g_file_get_uri (target);
7337 g_object_unref (target);
7338 }
7339 return target_uri;
7340 }
7341}

7380 * caja_file_is_user_special_directory
7381 *

7385 *
7386 * Returns: TRUE if @file is a special directory of the given kind.
7387 */
7388gboolean
7389caja_file_is_user_special_directory (CajaFile *file,
7390 GUserDirectory special_directory)
7391{
7392 gboolean is_special_dir;
7393 const gchar *special_dir;
7394

7396 is_special_dir = FALSE(0);
7397
7398 if (special_dir) {
7399 GFile *loc;
7400 GFile *special_gfile;
7401
7402 loc = caja_file_get_location (file);
7403 special_gfile = g_file_new_for_path (special_dir);
7404 is_special_dir = g_file_equal (loc, special_gfile);
7405 g_object_unref (special_gfile);
7406 g_object_unref (loc);
7407 }
7408
7409 return is_special_dir;
7410}

7496
7497/**
7498 * caja_file_is_binary
7499 *
7500 * Check if this file is a binary file.
7501 * This is private and is used to decide whether or not to show the diff
7502 * button in the file conflict dialog.
7503 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
7504 *
7505 * Returns: TRUE if @file is a binary file.
7506 *
7507 **/
7508gboolean
7509caja_file_is_binary (CajaFile *file)
7510{
7511 if (!caja_file_can_read(file))
7512 {
7513 return FALSE(0);
7514 }
7515
7516 gboolean is_binary = FALSE(0);
7517 int i = 0;
7518 FILE *fp;
7519
7520 /* Check the first 4096 bytes of the files. If these contains a 0,
7521 * we can assume the file is binary.
7522 * This idea is taken from python code of meld.
7523 */
7524
7525 fp = g_fopenfopen (g_file_get_path (caja_file_get_location (file)), "r");
7526 if (fp == NULL((void*)0))
7527 {
7528 return FALSE(0);
7529 }
7530
7531 while (!feof (fp)) {
7532 int c;
7533
7534 if (i > 4096) {
7535 break;
7536 }
7537 c = fgetc(fp);
7538 if (c == 0) {
7539 is_binary = TRUE(!(0));
7540 break;
7541 }
7542 i++;
7543 }
7544 fclose(fp);
7545
7546 return is_binary;
7547}
7548
7549/**
7550 * caja_file_is_executable
7551 *
7552 * Check if this file is executable at all.
7553 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
7554 *
7555 * Returns: TRUE if any of the execute bits are set. FALSE if
7556 * not, or if the permissions are unknown.
7557 *
7558 **/
7559gboolean
7560caja_file_is_executable (CajaFile *file)
7561{
7562 if (!file->details->has_permissions) {
7563 /* File's permissions field is not valid.
7564 * Can't access specific permissions, so return FALSE.
7565 */
7566 return FALSE(0);
7567 }
7568
7569 return file->details->can_execute;
7570}

7572/**
7573 * caja_file_peek_top_left_text
7574 *
7575 * Peek at the text from the top left of the file.
7576 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
7577 *
7578 * Returns: NULL if there is no text readable, otherwise, the text.
7579 * This string is owned by the file object and should not
7580 * be kept around or freed.
7581 *
7582 **/
7583char *
7584caja_file_peek_top_left_text (CajaFile *file,
7585 gboolean need_large_text,
7586 gboolean *needs_loading)
7587{
7588 g_return_val_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file), NULL)do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_680
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_680
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_680 = 0; _g_boolean_var_680; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); return (((void*)
0)); } } while (0);
7589
7590 if (!caja_file_should_get_top_left_text (file)) {
7591 if (needs_loading) {
7592 *needs_loading = FALSE(0);
7593 }
7594 return NULL((void*)0);
7595 }
7596
7597 if (needs_loading) {
7598 *needs_loading = !file->details->top_left_text_is_up_to_date;
7599 if (need_large_text) {
7600 *needs_loading |= file->details->got_top_left_text != file->details->got_large_top_left_text;
7601 }
7602 }
7603
7604 /* Show " ..." in the file until we read the contents in. */
7605 if (!file->details->got_top_left_text) {
7606
7607 if (caja_file_contains_text (file)) {
7608 return " ...";
7609 }
7610 return NULL((void*)0);
7611 }
7612
7613 /* Show what we read in. */
7614 return file->details->top_left_text;
7615}

7656
7657void
7658caja_file_mark_gone (CajaFile *file)
7659{
7660 CajaDirectory *directory;
7661
7662 if (file->details->is_gone)
7663 return;
7664
7665 file->details->is_gone = TRUE(!(0));
7666
7667 update_links_if_target (file);
7668
7669 /* Drop it from the symlink hash ! */
7670 remove_from_link_hash_table (file);
7671
7672 /* Let the directory know it's gone. */
7673 directory = file->details->directory;
7674 if (!caja_file_is_self_owned (file)) {
7675 caja_directory_remove_file (directory, file);
7676 }
7677
7678 caja_file_clear_info (file);
7679
7680 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 42429:
7681 * Maybe we can get rid of the name too eventually, but
7682 * for now that would probably require too many if statements
7683 * everywhere anyone deals with the name. Maybe we can give it
7684 * a hard-coded "<deleted>" name or something.
7685 */
7686}

7695caja_file_changed (CajaFile *file)
7696{

7698
7699 g_return_if_fail (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if ((__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_681

= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_681
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_681 = 0; _g_boolean_var_681; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const
char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); return; } } while
(0);
7700

7736/**
7737 * caja_file_emit_changed
7738 *
7739 * Emit a file changed signal.
7740 * This can only be called by the directory, since the directory
7741 * also has to emit a files_changed signal.
7742 *
7743 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
7744 **/
7745void
7746caja_file_emit_changed (CajaFile *file)
7747{
7748 GList *link_files, *p;
7749
7750 g_assert (CAJA_IS_FILE (file))do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_684
; if ((((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance
*) ((file)); GType __t = (caja_file_get_type()); gboolean __r
; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_684
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_684 = 0; _g_boolean_var_684; }), 1)
) ; else g_assertion_message_expr (((gchar*) 0), "caja-file.c"
, 7750, ((const char*) (__func__)), "CAJA_IS_FILE (file)"); }
while (0);
7751
7752 /* Invalidate the emblem compare cache. -- This is not the cleanest
7753 * place to do it but it is the one guaranteed bottleneck through
7754 * which all change notifications pass.
7755 */
7756 g_free (file->details->compare_by_emblem_cache);
7757 file->details->compare_by_emblem_cache = NULL((void*)0);
7758
7759 /* Send out a signal. */
7760 g_signal_emit (file, signals[CHANGED], 0, file);
7761
7762 /* Tell link files pointing to this object about the change. */
7763 link_files = get_link_files (file);
7764 for (p = link_files; p != NULL((void*)0); p = p->next) {
7765 if (p->data != file) {
7766 caja_file_changed (CAJA_FILE (p->data)((((CajaFile*) (void *) ((p->data))))));
7767 }
7768 }
7769 caja_file_list_free (link_files);
7770}

7805/**
7806 * caja_file_check_if_ready
7807 *
7808 * Check whether the values for a set of file attributes are
7809 * currently available, without doing any additional work. This
7810 * is useful for callers that want to reflect updated information
7811 * when it is ready but don't want to force the work required to
7812 * obtain the information, which might be slow network calls, e.g.
7813 *
7814 * @file: The file being queried.
7815 * @file_attributes: A bit-mask with the desired information.
7816 *
7817 * Return value: TRUE if all of the specified attributes are currently readable.
7818 */

; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&

= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) _g_boolean_var_687
= 1; else _g_boolean_var_687 = 0; _g_boolean_var_687; }), 1)
)) { } else { g_return_if_fail_warning (((gchar*) 0), ((const

*) ((file)))->g_class)))))))))->check_if_ready == ((void
*)0)) ? 0 : ((* ((((CajaFileClass*) (void *) ((((((GObjectClass

7923void
7924caja_file_invalidate_extension_info_internal (CajaFile *file)
7925{
7926 if (file->details->pending_info_providers)
7927 g_list_free_full (file->details->pending_info_providers, g_object_unref);
7928
7929 file->details->pending_info_providers =
7930 caja_extensions_get_for_type (CAJA_TYPE_INFO_PROVIDER(caja_info_provider_get_type ()));
7931}
7932
7933void
7934caja_file_invalidate_attributes_internal (CajaFile *file,
7935 CajaFileAttributes file_attributes)
7936{
7937 Request request;
7938
7939 if (file == NULL((void*)0)) {
7940 return;
7941 }
7942
7943 if (CAJA_IS_DESKTOP_ICON_FILE (file)(((__extension__ ({ GTypeInstance *__inst = (GTypeInstance*) (
(file)); GType __t = (caja_desktop_icon_file_get_type()); gboolean
__r; if (!__inst) __r = (0); else if (__inst->g_class &&
__inst->g_class->g_type == __t) __r = (!(0)); else __r
= g_type_check_instance_is_a (__inst, __t); __r; }))))) {
7944 /* Desktop icon files are always up to date.
7945 * If we invalidate their attributes they
7946 * will lose data, so we just ignore them.
7947 */
7948 return;
7949 }
7950
7951 request = caja_directory_set_up_request (file_attributes);
7952
7953 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_DIRECTORY_COUNT)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_DIRECTORY_COUNT)))) {
7954 invalidate_directory_count (file);
7955 }
7956 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_DEEP_COUNT)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_DEEP_COUNT)))) {
7957 invalidate_deep_counts (file);
7958 }
7959 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_MIME_LIST)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_MIME_LIST)))) {
7960 invalidate_mime_list (file);
7961 }
7962 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_FILE_INFO)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_FILE_INFO)))) {
7963 invalidate_file_info (file);
7964 }
7965 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_TOP_LEFT_TEXT)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_TOP_LEFT_TEXT)))) {
7966 invalidate_top_left_text (file);
7967 }
7968 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_LINK_INFO)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_LINK_INFO)))) {
7969 invalidate_link_info (file);
7970 }
7971 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_EXTENSION_INFO)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_EXTENSION_INFO)))) {
7972 caja_file_invalidate_extension_info_internal (file);
7973 }
7974 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_THUMBNAIL)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_THUMBNAIL)))) {
7975 invalidate_thumbnail (file);
7976 }
7977 if (REQUEST_WANTS_TYPE (request, REQUEST_MOUNT)((request) & (1<<(REQUEST_MOUNT)))) {
7978 invalidate_mount (file);
7979 }
7980
7981 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 45075: implement invalidating metadata */
7982}

8019/**
8020 * caja_file_invalidate_attributes
8021 *
8022 * Invalidate the specified attributes and force a reload.
8023 * @file: CajaFile representing the file in question.
8024 * @file_attributes: attributes to froget.
8025 **/
8026
8027void
8028caja_file_invalidate_attributes (CajaFile *file,
8029 CajaFileAttributes file_attributes)
8030{
8031 /* Cancel possible in-progress loads of any of these attributes */
8032 caja_directory_cancel_loading_file_attributes (file->details->directory,
8033 file,
8034 file_attributes);
8035
8036 /* Actually invalidate the values */
8037 caja_file_invalidate_attributes_internal (file, file_attributes);
8038
8039 caja_directory_add_file_to_work_queue (file->details->directory, file);
8040
8041 /* Kick off I/O if necessary */
8042 caja_directory_async_state_changed (file->details->directory);
8043}

8050 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DEEP_COUNTS |
8051 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY_ITEM_COUNT |
8052 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY_ITEM_MIME_TYPES |
8053 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT |
8054 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_LARGE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT |
8055 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_EXTENSION_INFO |
8056 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_THUMBNAIL |
8057 CAJA_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_MOUNT;
8058}

8066 caja_file_invalidate_attributes (file, all_attributes);
8067}
8068
8069/**
8070 * caja_file_dump
8071 *
8072 * Debugging call, prints out the contents of the file
8073 * fields.
8074 *
8075 * @file: file to dump.
8076 **/
8077void
8078caja_file_dump (CajaFile *file)
8079{
8080 long size = file->details->deep_size;
8081 long size_on_disk = file->details->deep_size_on_disk;
8082 char *uri;
8083 const char *file_kind;
8084
8085 uri = caja_file_get_uri (file);
8086 g_print ("uri: %s \n", uri);
8087 if (!file->details->got_file_info) {
8088 g_print ("no file info \n");
8089 } else if (file->details->get_info_failed) {
8090 g_print ("failed to get file info \n");
8091 } else {
8092 g_print ("size: %ld \n", size);
8093 g_print ("disk size: %ld \n", size_on_disk);
8094 switch (file->details->type) {
8095 case G_FILE_TYPE_REGULAR:
8096 file_kind = "regular file";
8097 break;
8098 case G_FILE_TYPE_DIRECTORY:
8099 file_kind = "folder";
8100 break;
8101 case G_FILE_TYPE_SPECIAL:
8102 file_kind = "special";
8103 break;
8104 case G_FILE_TYPE_SYMBOLIC_LINK:
8105 file_kind = "symbolic link";
8106 break;
8107 case G_FILE_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
8108 default:
8109 file_kind = "unknown";
8110 break;
8111 }
8112 g_print ("kind: %s \n", file_kind);
8113 if (file->details->type == G_FILE_TYPE_SYMBOLIC_LINK) {
8114 g_print ("link to %s \n", file->details->symlink_name);
8115 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 42430: add following of symlinks here */
8116 }
8117 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 42431: add permissions and other useful stuff here */
8118 }
8119 g_free (uri);
8120}

8171
8172static gboolean
8173get_attributes_for_default_sort_type (CajaFile *file,
8174 gboolean *is_download,
8175 gboolean *is_trash)
8176{
8177 gboolean is_download_dir, is_desktop_dir, is_trash_dir, retval;
8178
8179 *is_download = FALSE(0);
8180 *is_trash = FALSE(0);
8181 retval = FALSE(0);
8182
8183 /* special handling for certain directories */
8184 if (file && caja_file_is_directory (file)) {
8185 is_download_dir =
8186 caja_file_is_user_special_directory (file, G_USER_DIRECTORY_DOWNLOAD);
8187 is_desktop_dir =
8188 caja_file_is_user_special_directory (file, G_USER_DIRECTORY_DESKTOP);
8189 is_trash_dir =
8190 caja_file_is_in_trash (file);
8191
8192 if (is_download_dir && !is_desktop_dir) {
8193 *is_download = TRUE(!(0));
8194 retval = TRUE(!(0));
8195 } else if (is_trash_dir) {
8196 *is_trash = TRUE(!(0));
8197 retval = TRUE(!(0));
8198 }
8199 }
8200
8201 return retval;
8202}
8203
8204CajaFileSortType
8205caja_file_get_default_sort_type (CajaFile *file,
8206 gboolean *reversed)
8207{
8208 CajaFileSortType retval;
8209 gboolean is_download, is_trash, res;
8210
8211 retval = CAJA_FILE_SORT_NONE;
8212 is_download = is_trash = FALSE(0);
8213 res = get_attributes_for_default_sort_type (file, &is_download, &is_trash);
8214
8215 if (res) {
8216 if (is_download) {
8217 retval = CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_MTIME;
8218 } else if (is_trash) {
8219 retval = CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_TRASHED_TIME;
8220 }
8221
8222 if (reversed != NULL((void*)0)) {
8223 *reversed = res;
8224 }
8225 }
8226
8227 return retval;
8228}
8229
8230const gchar *
8231caja_file_get_default_sort_attribute (CajaFile *file,
8232 gboolean *reversed)
8233{
8234 const gchar *retval;
8235 gboolean is_download, is_trash, res;
8236
8237 retval = NULL((void*)0);
8238 is_download = is_trash = FALSE(0);
8239 res = get_attributes_for_default_sort_type (file, &is_download, &is_trash);
8240
8241 if (res) {
8242 if (is_download) {
8243 retval = g_quark_to_string (attribute_date_modified_q);
8244 } else if (is_trash) {
8245 retval = g_quark_to_string (attribute_trashed_on_q);
8246 }
8247
8248 if (reversed != NULL((void*)0)) {
8249 *reversed = res;
8250 }
8251 }
8252
8253 return retval;
8254}

8274static GList *ready_data_list = NULL((void*)0);
8275
8276typedef struct
8277{
8278 GList *file_list;
8279 GList *remaining_files;
8280 CajaFileListCallback callback;
8281 gpointer callback_data;
8282} FileListReadyData;
8283
8284static void
8285file_list_ready_data_free (FileListReadyData *data)
8286{
8287 GList *l;
8288
8289 l = g_list_find (ready_data_list, data);
8290 if (l != NULL((void*)0)) {
8291 ready_data_list = g_list_delete_link (ready_data_list, l);
8292
8293 caja_file_list_free (data->file_list);
8294 g_list_free (data->remaining_files);

8394
8395static char *
8396try_to_make_utf8 (const char *text, int *length)
8397{
8398 static const char *encodings_to_try[2];
8399 static int n_encodings_to_try = 0;
8400 gsize converted_length;
8401 GError *conversion_error;
8402 char *utf8_text;
8403 int i;
8404
8405 if (n_encodings_to_try == 0) {
8406 const char *charset;
8407 gboolean charset_is_utf8;
8408
8409 charset_is_utf8 = g_get_charset (&charset);
8410 if (!charset_is_utf8) {
8411 encodings_to_try[n_encodings_to_try++] = charset;
8412 }
8413
8414 if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (charset, "ISO-8859-1") != 0) {
8415 encodings_to_try[n_encodings_to_try++] = "ISO-8859-1";
8416 }
8417 }
8418
8419 utf8_text = NULL((void*)0);
8420 for (i = 0; i < n_encodings_to_try; i++) {
8421 conversion_error = NULL((void*)0);
8422 utf8_text = g_convert (text, *length,
8423 "UTF-8", encodings_to_try[i],
8424 NULL((void*)0), &converted_length, &conversion_error);
8425 if (utf8_text != NULL((void*)0)) {
8426 *length = converted_length;
8427 break;
8428 }
8429 g_error_free (conversion_error);
8430 }
8431
8432 return utf8_text;
8433}
8434
8435/* Extract the top left part of the read-in text. */
8436char *
8437caja_extract_top_left_text (const char *text,
8438 gboolean large,
8439 int length)
8440{
8441 GString* buffer;
8442 const gchar *in;
8443 const gchar *end;
8444 int line, i;
8445 gunichar c;
8446 char *text_copy;
8447 const char *utf8_end;
8448 gboolean validated;
8449 int max_bytes, max_lines, max_cols;
8450
8451 if (large) {
8452 max_bytes = CAJA_FILE_LARGE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT_MAXIMUM_BYTES10000;
8453 max_lines = CAJA_FILE_LARGE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT_MAXIMUM_LINES24;
8454 max_cols = CAJA_FILE_LARGE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT_MAXIMUM_CHARACTERS_PER_LINE80;
8455 } else {
8456 max_bytes = CAJA_FILE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT_MAXIMUM_BYTES1024;
8457 max_lines = CAJA_FILE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT_MAXIMUM_LINES5;
8458 max_cols = CAJA_FILE_TOP_LEFT_TEXT_MAXIMUM_CHARACTERS_PER_LINE10;
8459 }
8460
8461 text_copy = NULL((void*)0);
8462 if (text != NULL((void*)0)) {
8463 /* Might be a partial utf8 character at the end if we didn't read whole file */
8464 validated = g_utf8_validate (text, length, &utf8_end);
8465 if (!validated &&
8466 !(length >= max_bytes &&
8467 text + length - utf8_end < 6)) {
8468 text_copy = try_to_make_utf8 (text, &length);
8469 text = text_copy;
8470 } else if (!validated) {
8471 length = utf8_end - text;
8472 }
8473 }
8474
8475 if (text == NULL((void*)0) || length == 0) {
8476 return NULL((void*)0);
8477 }
8478
8479 buffer = g_string_new ("");
8480 end = text + length; in = text;
8481
8482 for (line = 0; line < max_lines; line++) {
8483 /* Extract one line. */
8484 for (i = 0; i < max_cols; ) {
8485 if (*in == '\n') {
8486 break;
8487 }
8488
8489 c = g_utf8_get_char (in);
8490
8491 if (g_unichar_isprint (c)) {
8492 g_string_append_unichar (buffer, c);
8493 i++;
8494 }
8495
8496 in = g_utf8_next_char (in)(char *)((in) + g_utf8_skip[*(const guchar *)(in)]);
8497 if (in == end) {
8498 goto done;
8499 }
8500 }
8501
8502 /* Skip the rest of the line. */
8503 while (*in != '\n') {
8504 if (++in == end) {
8505 goto done;
8506 }
8507 }
8508 if (++in == end) {
8509 goto done;
8510 }
8511
8512 /* Put a new-line separator in. */
8513 g_string_append_c(buffer, '\n')g_string_append_c_inline (buffer, '\n');
8514 }
8515 done:
8516 g_free (text_copy);
8517
8518 return g_string_free(buffer, FALSE)(__builtin_constant_p ((0)) ? (((0)) ? (g_string_free) ((buffer
), ((0))) : g_string_free_and_steal (buffer)) : (g_string_free
) ((buffer), ((0))));
8519}

8694caja_file_add_string_attribute (CajaFile *file,
8695 const char *attribute_name,
8696 const char *value)
8697{
8698 if (file->details->pending_info_providers) {
8699 /* Lazily create hashtable */
8700 if (!file->details->pending_extension_attributes) {
8701 file->details->pending_extension_attributes =
8702 g_hash_table_new_full (g_direct_hash, g_direct_equal,
8703 NULL((void*)0),
8704 (GDestroyNotify)g_free);
8705 }
8706 g_hash_table_insert (file->details->pending_extension_attributes,
8707 GINT_TO_POINTER (g_quark_from_string (attribute_name))((gpointer) (glong) (g_quark_from_string (attribute_name))),
8708 g_strdup (value)g_strdup_inline (value));
8709 } else {
8710 if (!file->details->extension_attributes) {
8711 file->details->extension_attributes =
8712 g_hash_table_new_full (g_direct_hash, g_direct_equal,
8713 NULL((void*)0),
8714 (GDestroyNotify)g_free);
8715 }
8716 g_hash_table_insert (file->details->extension_attributes,
8717 GINT_TO_POINTER (g_quark_from_string (attribute_name))((gpointer) (glong) (g_quark_from_string (attribute_name))),
8718 g_strdup (value)g_strdup_inline (value));
8719 }

8722}

8730void
8731caja_file_info_providers_done (CajaFile *file)
8732{
8733 g_list_free_full (file->details->extension_emblems, g_free);
8734 file->details->extension_emblems = file->details->pending_extension_emblems;
8735 file->details->pending_extension_emblems = NULL((void*)0);
8736
8737 if (file->details->extension_attributes) {
8738 g_hash_table_destroy (file->details->extension_attributes);
8739 }
8740
8741 file->details->extension_attributes = file->details->pending_extension_attributes;
8742 file->details->pending_extension_attributes = NULL((void*)0);
8743
8744 caja_file_changed (file);
8745}

8747static void
8748caja_file_info_iface_init (CajaFileInfoIface *iface)
8749{
8750 iface->is_gone = caja_file_is_gone;
8751 iface->get_name = caja_file_get_name;
8752 iface->get_file_type = caja_file_get_file_type;
8753 iface->get_location = caja_file_get_location;
8754 iface->get_uri = caja_file_get_uri;
8755 iface->get_parent_location = caja_file_get_parent_location;
8756 iface->get_parent_uri = caja_file_get_parent_uri;
8757 iface->get_parent_info = caja_file_get_parent;
8758 iface->get_mount = caja_file_get_mount;
8759 iface->get_uri_scheme = caja_file_get_uri_scheme;
8760 iface->get_activation_uri = caja_file_get_activation_uri;
8761 iface->get_mime_type = caja_file_get_mime_type;
8762 iface->is_mime_type = caja_file_is_mime_type;
8763 iface->is_directory = caja_file_is_directory;
8764 iface->can_write = caja_file_can_write;
8765 iface->add_emblem = caja_file_add_emblem;
8766 iface->get_string_attribute = caja_file_get_string_attribute;
8767 iface->add_string_attribute = caja_file_add_string_attribute;
8768 iface->invalidate_extension_info = caja_file_invalidate_extension_info;
8769}

8772
8773void
8774caja_self_check_file (void)
8775{
8776 CajaFile *file_1;
8777 CajaFile *file_2;
8778 GList *list;
8779
8780 /* refcount checks */
8781
8782 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (caja_directory_number_outstanding (), 0)do { eel_before_check ("caja_directory_number_outstanding ()"
, "caja-file.c", 8782); eel_check_integer_result (caja_directory_number_outstanding
(), 0); } while (0);
8783
8784 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///home/");
8785
8786 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_1)->ref_count, 1)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8786); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count, 1); } while (0);
8787 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_1->details->directory)->ref_count, 1)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_1->details->directory)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8787); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_1->details->directory)))))->ref_count
, 1); } while (0);
8788 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (caja_directory_number_outstanding (), 1)do { eel_before_check ("caja_directory_number_outstanding ()"
, "caja-file.c", 8788); eel_check_integer_result (caja_directory_number_outstanding
(), 1); } while (0);
8789
8790 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8791
8792 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (caja_directory_number_outstanding (), 0)do { eel_before_check ("caja_directory_number_outstanding ()"
, "caja-file.c", 8792); eel_check_integer_result (caja_directory_number_outstanding
(), 0); } while (0);
8793
8794 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///etc");
8795 file_2 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///usr");
8796
8797 list = NULL((void*)0);
8798 list = g_list_prepend (list, file_1);
8799 list = g_list_prepend (list, file_2);
8800
8801 caja_file_list_ref (list);
8802
8803 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_1)->ref_count, 2)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8803); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count, 2); } while (0);
8804 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_2)->ref_count, 2)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_2)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8804); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_2)))))->ref_count, 2); } while (0);
8805
8806 caja_file_list_unref (list);
8807
8808 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_1)->ref_count, 1)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8808); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count, 1); } while (0);
8809 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_2)->ref_count, 1)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_2)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8809); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_2)))))->ref_count, 1); } while (0);
8810
8811 caja_file_list_free (list);
8812
8813 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (caja_directory_number_outstanding (), 0)do { eel_before_check ("caja_directory_number_outstanding ()"
, "caja-file.c", 8813); eel_check_integer_result (caja_directory_number_outstanding
(), 0); } while (0);
8814
8815 /* name checks */
8816 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///home/");
8817
8818 EEL_CHECK_STRING_RESULT (caja_file_get_name (file_1), "home")do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_get_name (file_1)", "caja-file.c"
, 8818); eel_check_string_result (caja_file_get_name (file_1)
, "home"); } while (0);
8819
8820 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///home/") == file_1, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_get_by_uri (\"file:///home/\") == file_1"
, "caja-file.c", 8820); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_get_by_uri
("file:///home/") == file_1, (!(0))); } while (0);
8821 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8822
8823 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///home") == file_1, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_get_by_uri (\"file:///home\") == file_1"
, "caja-file.c", 8823); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_get_by_uri
("file:///home") == file_1, (!(0))); } while (0);
8824 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8825
8826 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8827
8828 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///home");
8829 EEL_CHECK_STRING_RESULT (caja_file_get_name (file_1), "home")do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_get_name (file_1)", "caja-file.c"
, 8829); eel_check_string_result (caja_file_get_name (file_1)
, "home"); } while (0);
8830 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8831
8832#if 0
8833 /* ALEX: I removed this, because it was breaking distchecks.
8834 * It used to work, but when canonical uris changed from
8835 * foo: to foo:/// it broke. I don't expect it to matter
8836 * in real life */
8837 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri (":");
8838 EEL_CHECK_STRING_RESULT (caja_file_get_name (file_1), ":")do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_get_name (file_1)", "caja-file.c"
, 8838); eel_check_string_result (caja_file_get_name (file_1)
, ":"); } while (0);
8839 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8840#endif
8841
8842 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("eazel:");
8843 EEL_CHECK_STRING_RESULT (caja_file_get_name (file_1), "eazel")do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_get_name (file_1)", "caja-file.c"
, 8843); eel_check_string_result (caja_file_get_name (file_1)
, "eazel"); } while (0);
8844 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8845
8846 /* sorting */
8847 file_1 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///etc");
8848 file_2 = caja_file_get_by_uri ("file:///usr");
8849
8850 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_1)->ref_count, 1)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8850); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_1)))))->ref_count, 1); } while (0);
8851 EEL_CHECK_INTEGER_RESULT (G_OBJECT (file_2)->ref_count, 1)do { eel_before_check ("((((GObject*) (void *) ((file_2)))))->ref_count"
, "caja-file.c", 8851); eel_check_integer_result (((((GObject
*) (void *) ((file_2)))))->ref_count, 1); } while (0);
8852
8853 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, FALSE, FALSE) < 0, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (0)) < 0"
, "caja-file.c", 8853); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_compare_for_sort
(file_1, file_2, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (0)) <
0, (!(0))); } while (0);
8854 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, FALSE, TRUE) > 0, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_2, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (!(0))) > 0"
, "caja-file.c", 8854); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_compare_for_sort
(file_1, file_2, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (!(0))
) > 0, (!(0))); } while (0);
8855 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, FALSE, FALSE) == 0, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (0)) == 0"
, "caja-file.c", 8855); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_compare_for_sort
(file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (0)) ==
0, (!(0))); } while (0);
8856 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, TRUE, FALSE) == 0, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (!(0)), (0)) == 0"
, "caja-file.c", 8856); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_compare_for_sort
(file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (!(0)), (0)
) == 0, (!(0))); } while (0);
8857 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, FALSE, TRUE) == 0, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (!(0))) == 0"
, "caja-file.c", 8857); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_compare_for_sort
(file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (0), (!(0))
) == 0, (!(0))); } while (0);
8858 EEL_CHECK_BOOLEAN_RESULT (caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, TRUE, TRUE) == 0, TRUE)do { eel_before_check ("caja_file_compare_for_sort (file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (!(0)), (!(0))) == 0"
, "caja-file.c", 8858); eel_check_boolean_result (caja_file_compare_for_sort
(file_1, file_1, CAJA_FILE_SORT_BY_DISPLAY_NAME, (!(0)), (!(
0))) == 0, (!(0))); } while (0);
8859
8860 caja_file_unref (file_1);
8861 caja_file_unref (file_2);
8862}
